{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "1SA"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["1 Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The First Book of Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["1 Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["1Sa \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["The First Book of Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 1:1"}, "Now there was a certain man of Ramathaim Zophim, of the hill country of Ephraim, and his name was Elkanah, the son of\nJeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 1:2"}, "He had two wives. The name of one was Hannah, and the name of the other Peninnah. Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no\nchildren. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 1:3"}, "This man went up out of his city from year to year to worship and to sacrifice to the\nLORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of Armies in Shiloh. The two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, priests to the LORD, were there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 1:4"}, "When the day came that Elkanah sacrificed, he gave to Peninnah his wife, and to all her sons and her daughters, portions;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 1:5"}, "but to Hannah he gave a double portion, for he loved Hannah, but the LORD had shut up her womb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 1:6"}, "Her rival provoked her severely, to irritate her, because the LORD had shut up her womb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 1:7"}, "So year by year, when she went up to the LORD\u2019s house, her rival provoked her. Therefore she wept, and didn\u2019t eat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 1:8"}, "Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201cHannah, why do you weep? Why don\u2019t you eat? Why is your heart grieved? Am I not better\nto you than ten sons?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 1:9"}, "So Hannah rose up after they had finished eating and drinking in Shiloh. Now Eli the priest was sitting on his seat by the\ndoorpost of the LORD\u2019s temple. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 1:10"}, "She was in bitterness of soul, and prayed to the LORD, weeping bitterly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 1:11"}, "She vowed a vow, and said, \u201cThe LORD of Armies, if you will indeed look at the affliction of your servant, and remember\nme, and not forget your servant, but will give to your servant a boy, then I will give him to the LORD all the days of his\nlife, and no razor shall come on his head.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 1:12"}, "As she continued praying before the LORD, Eli saw her mouth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 1:13"}, "Now Hannah spoke in her heart. Only her lips moved, but her voice was not heard. Therefore Eli thought she was drunk.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 1:14"}, "Eli said to her, \u201cHow long will you be drunk? Get rid of your wine!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 1:15"}, "Hannah answered, \u201cNo, my lord, I am a woman of a sorrowful spirit. I have not been drinking wine or strong drink, but I\npoured out my soul before the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 1:16"}, "Don\u2019t consider your servant a wicked woman; for I have been speaking out of the abundance of my complaint and my\nprovocation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 1:17"}, "Then Eli answered, \u201cGo in peace; and may Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:17\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d (Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of Israel grant your petition that you have asked of him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 1:18"}, "She said, \u201cLet your servant find favour in your sight.\u201d So the woman went her way, and ate; and her facial expression\nwasn\u2019t sad any more. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 1:19"}, "They rose up in the morning early and worshipped the LORD, then returned and came to their house to Ramah. Then Elkanah\nknew Hannah his wife; and the LORD remembered her. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 1:20"}, "When the time had come, Hannah conceived, and bore a son; and she named him\nSamuel,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Samuel sounds like the Hebrew for \u201cheard by\nAllah.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cBecause I have asked him of the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 1:21"}, "The man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer to the LORD the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 1:22"}, "But Hannah didn\u2019t go up; for she said to her husband, \u201cNot until the child is weaned; then I will bring him, that he may\nappear before the LORD, and stay there forever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 1:23"}, "Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201cDo what seems good to you. Wait until you have weaned him; only may the LORD establish\nhis word.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So the woman waited and nursed her son, until she weaned him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 1:24"}, "When she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bulls, and one\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of meal, and a container of wine, and brought him to the LORD\u2019s house in Shiloh. The child was young.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 1:25"}, "They killed the bull, and brought the child to Eli. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 1:26"}, "She said, \u201cOh, my lord, as your soul lives, my lord, I am the woman who stood by you here, praying to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 1:27"}, "I prayed for this child; and the LORD has given me my petition which I asked of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 1:28"}, "Therefore I have also given him to the LORD. As long as he lives he is given to the LORD.\u201d He worshipped the LORD there.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 2:1"}, "Hannah prayed, and said: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cMy heart exults in the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My horn is exalted in the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["My mouth is enlarged over my enemies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because I rejoice in your salvation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 2:2"}, "There is no one as holy as the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For there is no one besides you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor is there any rock like our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 2:3"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t keep talking so exceedingly proudly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t let arrogance come out of your mouth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For the LORD is Allah of knowledge. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["By him actions are weighed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 2:4"}, "\u201cThe bows of the mighty men are broken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who stumbled are armed with strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 2:5"}, "Those who were full have hired themselves out for bread. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who were hungry are satisfied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, the barren has borne seven. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She who has many children languishes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 2:6"}, "\u201cThe LORD kills, and makes alive. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He brings down to Sheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and brings up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 2:7"}, "The LORD makes poor, and makes rich. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He brings low, he also lifts up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 2:8"}, "He raises up the poor out of the dust. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He lifts up the needy from the dunghill, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["To make them sit with princes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and inherit the throne of glory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For the pillars of the earth are the LORD\u2019s. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has set the world on them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 2:9"}, "He will keep the feet of his holy ones, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the wicked shall be put to silence in darkness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for no man shall prevail by strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 2:10"}, "Those who strive with the LORD shall be broken to pieces. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will thunder against them in the sky. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe LORD will judge the ends of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will give strength to his king, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and exalt the horn of his anointed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 2:11"}, "Elkanah went to Ramah to his house. The child served the LORD before Eli the priest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 2:12"}, "Now the sons of Eli were wicked men. They didn\u2019t know the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 2:13"}, "The custom of the priests with the people was that when anyone offered a sacrifice, the priest\u2019s servant came while the\nmeat was boiling, with a fork of three teeth in his hand; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 2:14"}, "and he stabbed it into the pan, or kettle, or cauldron, or pot. The priest took all that the fork brought up for himself.\nThey did this to all the Israelites who came there to Shiloh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 2:15"}, "Yes, before they burnt the fat, the priest\u2019s servant came, and said to the man who sacrificed, \u201cGive meat to roast for\nthe priest; for he will not accept boiled meat from you, but raw.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 2:16"}, "If the man said to him, \u201cLet the fat be burnt first, and then take as much as your soul desires;\u201d then he would say, \u201cNo,\nbut you shall give it to me now; and if not, I will take it by force.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 2:17"}, "The sin of the young men was very great before the LORD; for the men despised the LORD\u2019s offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 2:18"}, "But Samuel ministered before the LORD, being a child, clothed with a linen ephod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 2:19"}, "Moreover his mother made him a little robe, and brought it to him from year to year, when she came up with her husband to\noffer the yearly sacrifice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 2:20"}, "Eli blessed Elkanah and his wife, and said, \u201cMay The LORD give you\noffspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " from this woman for the petition which was asked of the LORD.\u201d Then they went to their\nown home. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 2:21"}, "The LORD visited Hannah, and she conceived, and bore three sons and two daughters. The child Samuel grew before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 2:22"}, "Now Eli was very old; and he heard all that his sons did to all Israel, and how that they slept with the women who served\nat the door of the Tent of Meeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 2:23"}, "He said to them, \u201cWhy do you do such things? For I hear of your evil dealings from all this people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 2:24"}, "No, my sons; for it is not a good report that I hear! You make the LORD\u2019s people disobey.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 2:25"}, "If one man sins against another, Allah will judge him; but if a man sins against the LORD, who will intercede for him?\u201d\nNotwithstanding, they didn\u2019t listen to the voice of their father, because the LORD intended to kill them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 2:26"}, "The child Samuel grew on, and increased in favour both with the LORD, and also with men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 2:27"}, "A man of Allah came to Eli, and said to him, \u201cThe LORD says, \u2018Did I reveal myself to the house of your father, when they\nwere in Egypt in bondage to Pharaoh\u2019s house? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 2:28"}, "Didn\u2019t I choose him out of all the tribes of Israel to be my priest, to go up to my altar, to burn incense, to wear an\nephod before me? Didn\u2019t I give to the house of your father all the offerings of the children of Israel made by fire?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 2:29"}, "Why do you kick at my sacrifice and at my offering, which I have commanded in my habitation, and honour your sons above\nme, to make yourselves fat with the best of all the offerings of Israel my people?\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 2:30"}, "\u201cTherefore the LORD, Allah of Israel, says, \u2018I said indeed that your house, and the house of your father, should walk\nbefore me forever.\u2019 But now the LORD says, \u2018Far be it from me; for those who honour me I will honour, and those who despise me\nwill be cursed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 2:31"}, "Behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " the days come, that I will cut off your arm, and the arm of your father\u2019s house, that there will not be\nan old man in your house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 2:32"}, "You will see the affliction of my habitation, in all the wealth which I will give Israel; and there shall not be an old\nman in your house forever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 2:33"}, "The man of yours, whom I don\u2019t cut off from my altar, will consume your\neyes", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, blind your eyes with tears"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and grieve your heart; and all the increase of your house will die in\nthe flower of their age. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 2:34"}, "\u201c\u2018This will be the sign to you, that will come on your two sons, on Hophni and Phinehas: in one day they will both die.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 2:35"}, "I will raise up a faithful priest for myself, that will do according to that which is in my heart and in my mind. I will\nbuild him a sure house; and he will walk before my anointed forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1SA 2:36"}, "It will happen, that everyone who is left in your house will come and bow down to him for a piece of silver and a loaf of\nbread, and will say, \u201cPlease put me into one of the priests\u2019 offices, that I may eat a morsel of bread.\u201d\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 3:1"}, "The child Samuel ministered to the LORD before Eli. The LORD\u2019s word was rare in those days. There were not many visions,\nthen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 3:2"}, "At that time, when Eli was laid down in his place (now his eyes had begun to grow dim, so that he could not see),\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 3:3"}, "and Allah\u2019s lamp hadn\u2019t yet gone out, and Samuel had laid down in the LORD\u2019s temple, where Allah\u2019s ark was;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 3:4"}, "The LORD called Samuel; and he said, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 3:5"}, "He ran to Eli, and said, \u201cHere I am; for you called me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI didn\u2019t call. Lie down again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He went and lay down. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 3:6"}, "The LORD called yet again, \u201cSamuel!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samuel arose and went to Eli, and said, \u201cHere I am; for you called me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cI didn\u2019t call, my son. Lie down again.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 3:7"}, "Now Samuel didn\u2019t yet know the LORD, neither was the LORD\u2019s word yet revealed to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 3:8"}, "The LORD called Samuel again the third time. He arose and went to Eli, and said, \u201cHere I am; for you called me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Eli perceived that the LORD had called the child. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 3:9"}, "Therefore Eli said to Samuel, \u201cGo, lie down. It shall be, if he calls you, that you shall say, \u2018Speak, the LORD; for your\nservant hears.\u2019\u201d So Samuel went and lay down in his place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 3:10"}, "The LORD came, and stood, and called as at other times, \u201cSamuel! Samuel!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Samuel said, \u201cSpeak; for your servant hears.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 3:11"}, "The LORD said to Samuel, \u201cBehold, I will do a thing in Israel, at which both the ears of everyone who hears it will\ntingle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 3:12"}, "In that day I will perform against Eli all that I have spoken concerning his house, from the beginning even to the end.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 3:13"}, "For I have told him that I will judge his house forever, for the iniquity which he knew, because his sons brought a curse\non themselves, and he didn\u2019t restrain them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 3:14"}, "Therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli, that the iniquity of Eli\u2019s house shall not be removed with sacrifice or\noffering forever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 3:15"}, "Samuel lay until the morning, and opened the doors of the LORD\u2019s house. Samuel feared to show Eli the vision.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 3:16"}, "Then Eli called Samuel, and said, \u201cSamuel, my son!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 3:17"}, "He said, \u201cWhat is the thing that he has spoken to you? Please don\u2019t hide it from me. Allah do so to you, and more also,\nif you hide anything from me of all the things that he spoke to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 3:18"}, "Samuel told him every bit, and hid nothing from him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cIt is the LORD. Let him do what seems good to him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 3:19"}, "Samuel grew, and the LORD was with him, and let none of his words fall to the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 3:20"}, "All Israel from Dan even to Beersheba knew that Samuel was established to be a prophet of the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 3:21"}, "The LORD appeared again in Shiloh; for the LORD revealed himself to Samuel in Shiloh by the LORD\u2019s word.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "nb", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 4:1"}, "The word of Samuel came to all Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Now Israel went out against the Philistines to battle, and encamped beside Ebenezer; and the Philistines encamped in Aphek.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 4:2"}, "The Philistines put themselves in array against Israel. When they joined battle, Israel was defeated by the Philistines,\nwho killed about four thousand men of the army in the field. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 4:3"}, "When the people had come into the camp, the elders of Israel said, \u201cWhy has the LORD defeated us today before the\nPhilistines? Let\u2019s get the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant out of Shiloh and bring it to us, that it may come amongst us, and save\nus out of the hand of our enemies.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 4:4"}, "So the people sent to Shiloh; and they brought from there the ark of the covenant of the LORD of Armies, who sits above\nthe cherubim: and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of the covenant of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 4:5"}, "When the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant came into the camp, all Israel shouted with a great shout, so that the earth rang\nagain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 4:6"}, "When the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, \u201cWhat does the noise of this great shout in the camp of the\nHebrews mean?\u201d They understood that the LORD\u2019s ark had come into the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 4:7"}, "The Philistines were afraid, for they said, \u201cAllah has come into the camp.\u201d They said, \u201cWoe to us! For there has not been\nsuch a thing before. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 4:8"}, "Woe to us! Who shall deliver us out of the hand of these mighty gods? These are the gods that struck the Egyptians with\nall kinds of plagues in the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 4:9"}, "Be strong, and behave like men, O you Philistines, that you not be servants to the Hebrews, as they have been to you.\nStrengthen yourselves like men, and fight!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 4:10"}, "The Philistines fought, and Israel was defeated, and each man fled to his tent. There was a very great slaughter; for\nthirty thousand footmen of Israel fell. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 4:11"}, "Allah\u2019s ark was taken; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were slain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 4:12"}, "A man of Benjamin ran out of the army, and came to Shiloh the same day, with his clothes torn, and with dirt on his head.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 4:13"}, "When he came, behold, Eli was sitting on his seat by the road watching; for his heart trembled for Allah\u2019s ark. When the\nman came into the city and told about it, all the city cried out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 4:14"}, "When Eli heard the noise of the crying, he said, \u201cWhat does the noise of this tumult mean?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The man hurried, and came and told Eli. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 4:15"}, "Now Eli was ninety-eight years old. His eyes were set, so that he could not see.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 4:16"}, "The man said to Eli, \u201cI am he who came out of the army, and I fled today out of the army.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHow did the matter go, my son?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 4:17"}, "He who brought the news answered, \u201cIsrael has fled before the Philistines, and there has been also a great slaughter\namongst the people. Your two sons also, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead, and Allah\u2019s ark has been captured.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 4:18"}, "When he made mention of Allah\u2019s ark, Eli fell from off his seat backward by the side of the gate; and his neck broke, and\nhe died; for he was an old man, and heavy. He had judged Israel forty years.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 4:19"}, "His daughter-in-law, Phinehas\u2019 wife, was with child, near to giving birth. When she heard the news that Allah\u2019s ark was\ntaken, and that her father-in-law and her husband were dead, she bowed herself and gave birth; for her pains came on her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 4:20"}, "About the time of her death the women who stood by her said to her, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid; for you have given birth to a son.\u201d\nBut she didn\u2019t answer, neither did she regard it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 4:21"}, "She named the child Ichabod,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cIchabod\u201d means \u201cno\nglory\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cThe glory has departed from Israel;\u201d because Allah\u2019s ark was taken, and because of her father-in-law and\nher husband. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 4:22"}, "She said, \u201cThe glory has departed from Israel; for Allah\u2019s ark has been taken.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 5:1"}, "Now the Philistines had taken Allah\u2019s ark, and they brought it from Ebenezer to Ashdod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 5:2"}, "The Philistines took Allah\u2019s ark, and brought it into the house of Dagon, and set it by Dagon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 5:3"}, "When the people of Ashdod arose early on the next day, behold, Dagon had fallen on his face to the ground before the\nLORD\u2019s ark. They took Dagon, and set him in his place again. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 5:4"}, "When they arose early on the following morning, behold, Dagon had fallen on his face to the ground before the LORD\u2019s ark;\nand the head of Dagon and both the palms of his hands were cut off on the threshold. Only Dagon\u2019s torso was intact.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 5:5"}, "Therefore neither the priests of Dagon, nor any who come into Dagon\u2019s house, step on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod, to\nthis day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 5:6"}, "But the LORD\u2019s hand was heavy on the people of Ashdod, and he destroyed them, and struck them with tumours, even Ashdod\nand its borders. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 5:7"}, "When the men of Ashdod saw that it was so, they said, \u201cThe ark of Allah of Israel shall not stay with us; for his hand is\nsevere on us, and on Dagon our god.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 5:8"}, "They sent therefore and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines, and said, \u201cWhat shall we do with the ark of\nAllah of Israel?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered, \u201cLet the ark of Allah of Israel be carried over to Gath.\u201d They carried the ark of Allah of Israel there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 5:9"}, "It was so, that after they had carried it there, the LORD\u2019s hand was against the city with a very great confusion; and he\nstruck the men of the city, both small and great so that tumours broke out on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 5:10"}, "So they sent Allah\u2019s ark to Ekron. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["As Allah\u2019s ark came to Ekron, the Ekronites cried out, saying, \u201cThey have brought the ark of Allah of Israel here to us, to\nkill us and our people.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 5:11"}, "They sent therefore and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines, and they said, \u201cSend the ark of Allah of\nIsrael away, and let it go again to its own place, that it not kill us and our people.\u201d For there was a deadly confusion\nthroughout all the city. The hand of Allah was very heavy there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 5:12"}, "The men who didn\u2019t die were struck with the tumours; and the cry of the city went up to heaven.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 6:1"}, "The LORD\u2019s ark was in the country of the Philistines seven months.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 6:2"}, "The Philistines called for the priests and the diviners, saying, \u201cWhat shall we do with the LORD\u2019s ark? Show us how we\nshould send it to its place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 6:3"}, "They said, \u201cIf you send away the ark of Allah of Israel, don\u2019t send it empty; but by all means return a trespass offering\nto him. Then you will be healed, and it will be known to you why his hand is not removed from you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 6:4"}, "Then they said, \u201cWhat should the trespass offering be which we shall return to him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cFive golden tumours, and five golden mice, for the number of the lords of the Philistines; for one plague was on\nyou all, and on your lords. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 6:5"}, "Therefore you shall make images of your tumours, and images of your mice that mar the land; and you shall give glory to\nAllah of Israel. Perhaps he will release his hand from you, from your gods, and from your land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 6:6"}, "Why then do you harden your hearts, as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened their hearts? When he had worked wonderfully\namongst them, didn\u2019t they let the people go, and they departed? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 6:7"}, "\u201cNow therefore take and prepare yourselves a new cart, and two milk cows, on which there has come no yoke; and tie the\ncows to the cart, and bring their calves home from them; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 6:8"}, "and take the LORD\u2019s ark, and lay it on the cart. Put the jewels of gold, which you return him for a trespass offering, in\na coffer by its side; and send it away, that it may go. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 6:9"}, "Behold; if it goes up by the way of its own border to Beth Shemesh, then he has done us this great evil; but if not, then\nwe shall know that it is not his hand that struck us. It was a chance that happened to us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 6:10"}, "The men did so, and took two milk cows, and tied them to the cart, and shut up their calves at home.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 6:11"}, "They put the LORD\u2019s ark on the cart, and the coffer with the golden mice and the images of their tumours.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 6:12"}, "The cows took the straight way by the way to Beth Shemesh. They went along the highway, lowing as they went, and didn\u2019t\nturn away to the right hand or to the left; and the lords of the Philistines went after them to the border of Beth Shemesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 6:13"}, "The people of Beth Shemesh were reaping their wheat harvest in the valley; and they lifted up their eyes, and saw the\nark, and rejoiced to see it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 6:14"}, "The cart came into the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh, and stood there, where there was a great stone. Then they split\nthe wood of the cart, and offered up the cows for a burnt offering to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 6:15"}, "The Levites took down the LORD\u2019s ark, and the box that was with it, in which the jewels of gold were, and put them on the\ngreat stone; and the men of Beth Shemesh offered burnt offerings and sacrificed sacrifices the same day to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 6:16"}, "When the five lords of the Philistines had seen it, they returned to Ekron the same day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 6:17"}, "These are the golden tumours which the Philistines returned for a trespass offering to the LORD: for Ashdod one, for Gaza\none, for Ashkelon one, for Gath one, for Ekron one; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 6:18"}, "and the golden mice, according to the number of all the cities of the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both of\nfortified cities and of country villages, even to the great stone, on which they set down the LORD\u2019s ark. That stone remains to\nthis day in the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 6:19"}, "He struck of the men of Beth Shemesh, because they had looked into the LORD\u2019s ark, he struck fifty thousand and seventy\nof the men. Then the people mourned, because the LORD had struck the people with a great slaughter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 6:20"}, "The men of Beth Shemesh said, \u201cWho is able to stand before the LORD, this holy Allah? To whom shall he go up from us?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 6:21"}, "They sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kiriath Jearim, saying, \u201cThe Philistines have brought back the LORD\u2019s ark.\nCome down, and bring it up to yourselves.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 7:1"}, "The men of Kiriath Jearim came, and took the LORD\u2019s ark, and brought it into Abinadab\u2019s house on the hill, and consecrated\nEleazar his son to keep the LORD\u2019s ark. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 7:2"}, "From the day that the ark stayed in Kiriath Jearim, the time was long; for it was twenty years; and all the house of\nIsrael lamented after the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 7:3"}, "Samuel spoke to all the house of Israel, saying, \u201cIf you are returning to the LORD with all your heart, then put away the\nforeign gods and the Ashtaroth from amongst you, and direct your hearts to the LORD, and serve him only; and he will deliver\nyou out of the hand of the Philistines.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 7:4"}, "Then the children of Israel removed the Baals and the Ashtaroth, and served the LORD only.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 7:5"}, "Samuel said, \u201cGather all Israel to Mizpah, and I will pray to the LORD for you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 7:6"}, "They gathered together to Mizpah, and drew water, and poured it out before the LORD, and fasted on that day, and said\nthere, \u201cWe have sinned against the LORD.\u201d Samuel judged the children of Israel in Mizpah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 7:7"}, "When the Philistines heard that the children of Israel were gathered together at Mizpah, the lords of the Philistines went\nup against Israel. When the children of Israel heard it, they were afraid of the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 7:8"}, "The children of Israel said to Samuel, \u201cDon\u2019t stop crying to the LORD our Allah for us, that he will save us out of the\nhand of the Philistines.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 7:9"}, "Samuel took a suckling lamb, and offered it for a whole burnt offering to the LORD. Samuel cried to the LORD for Israel;\nand the LORD answered him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 7:10"}, "As Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Philistines came near to battle against Israel; but the LORD thundered\nwith a great thunder on that day on the Philistines, and confused them; and they were struck down before Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 7:11"}, "The men of Israel went out of Mizpah, and pursued the Philistines, and struck them, until they came under Beth Kar.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 7:12"}, "Then Samuel took a stone, and set it between Mizpah and Shen, and called its name\nEbenezer,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cEbenezer\u201d means \u201cstone of help\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cThe LORD helped us until now.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 7:13"}, "So the Philistines were subdued, and they stopped coming within the border of Israel. The LORD\u2019s hand was against the\nPhilistines all the days of Samuel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 7:14"}, "The cities which the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored to Israel, from Ekron even to Gath; and Israel\nrecovered its border out of the hand of the Philistines. There was peace between Israel and the Amorites.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 7:15"}, "Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 7:16"}, "He went from year to year in a circuit to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah; and he judged Israel in all those places.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 7:17"}, "His return was to Ramah, for his house was there; and he judged Israel there; and he built an altar to the LORD there.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 8:1"}, "When Samuel was old, he made his sons judges over Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 8:2"}, "Now the name of his firstborn was Joel; and the name of his second, Abijah. They were judges in Beersheba.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 8:3"}, "His sons didn\u2019t walk in his ways, but turned away after dishonest gain, took bribes, and perverted justice.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 8:4"}, "Then all the elders of Israel gathered themselves together and came to Samuel to Ramah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 8:5"}, "They said to him, \u201cBehold, you are old, and your sons don\u2019t walk in your ways. Now make us a king to judge us like all the\nnations.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 8:6"}, "But the thing displeased Samuel, when they said, \u201cGive us a king to judge us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samuel prayed to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 8:7"}, "The LORD said to Samuel, \u201cListen to the voice of the people in all that they tell you; for they have not rejected you, but\nthey have rejected me as the king over them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 8:8"}, "According to all the works which they have done since the day that I brought them up out of Egypt even to this day, in\nthat they have forsaken me, and served other gods, so they also do to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 8:9"}, "Now therefore listen to their voice. However you shall protest solemnly to them, and shall show them the way of the king\nwho will reign over them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 8:10"}, "Samuel told all the LORD\u2019s words to the people who asked him for a king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 8:11"}, "He said, \u201cThis will be the way of the king who shall reign over you: he will take your sons, and appoint them as his\nservants, for his chariots, and to be his horsemen; and they will run before his chariots.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 8:12"}, "He will appoint them to him for captains of thousands, and captains of fifties; and he will assign some to plough his\nground, and to reap his harvest, and to make his instruments of war, and the instruments of his chariots.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 8:13"}, "He will take your daughters to be perfumers, to be cooks, and to be bakers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 8:14"}, "He will take your fields, your vineyards, and your olive groves, even their best, and give them to his servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 8:15"}, "He will take one tenth of your seed, and of your vineyards, and give it to his officers, and to his servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 8:16"}, "He will take your male servants, your female servants, your best young men, and your donkeys, and assign them to his own\nwork. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 8:17"}, "He will take one tenth of your flocks; and you will be his servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 8:18"}, "You will cry out in that day because of your king whom you will have chosen for yourselves; and the LORD will not answer\nyou in that day.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 8:19"}, "But the people refused to listen to the voice of Samuel; and they said, \u201cNo; but we will have a king over us,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 8:20"}, "that we also may be like all the nations, and that our king may judge us, and go out before us, and fight our battles.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 8:21"}, "Samuel heard all the words of the people, and he rehearsed them in the ears of the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 8:22"}, "The LORD said to Samuel, \u201cListen to their voice, and make them a king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samuel said to the men of Israel, \u201cEveryone go to your own city.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 9:1"}, "Now there was a man of Benjamin, whose name was Kish, the son of Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Becorath, the son of\nAphiah, the son of a Benjamite, a mighty man of valour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 9:2"}, "He had a son, whose name was Saul, an impressive young man; and there was not amongst the children of Israel a better\nperson than he. From his shoulders and upward he was taller than any of the people.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 9:3"}, "The donkeys of Kish, Saul\u2019s father, were lost. Kish said to Saul his son, \u201cNow take one of the servants with you, and\narise, go look for the donkeys.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 9:4"}, "He passed through the hill country of Ephraim, and passed through the land of Shalishah, but they didn\u2019t find them. Then\nthey passed through the land of Shaalim, and they weren\u2019t there. Then he passed through the land of the Benjamites, but they\ndidn\u2019t find them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 9:5"}, "When they had come to the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant who was with him, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s return, lest my father\nstop caring about the donkeys, and be anxious for us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 9:6"}, "The servant said to him, \u201cBehold now, there is a man of Allah in this city, and he is a man who is held in honour. All\nthat he says surely happens. Now let\u2019s go there. Perhaps he can tell us which way to go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 9:7"}, "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201cBut, behold, if we go, what should we bring the man? For the bread is spent in our sacks,\nand there is not a present to bring to the man of Allah. What do we have?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 9:8"}, "The servant answered Saul again, and said, \u201cBehold, I have in my hand the fourth part of a\nshekel", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 1/4 shekel would be a small coin of about 2.5\ngrams."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver. I will give that to the man of Allah, to tell us our way.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 9:9"}, "(In earlier times in Israel, when a man went to enquire of Allah, he said, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s go to the seer;\u201d for he who is now\ncalled a prophet was before called a seer.) \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 9:10"}, "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201cWell said. Come! Let\u2019s go.\u201d So they went to the city where the man of Allah was.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 9:11"}, "As they went up the ascent to the city, they found young maidens going out to draw water, and said to them, \u201cIs the seer\nhere?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 9:12"}, "They answered them, and said, \u201cHe is. Behold, he is before you. Hurry now, for he has come today into the city; for the\npeople have a sacrifice today in the high place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 9:13"}, "As soon as you have come into the city, you will immediately find him, before he goes up to the high place to eat; for\nthe people will not eat until he comes, because he blesses the sacrifice. Afterwards those who are invited eat. Now therefore\ngo up; for at this time you will find him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 9:14"}, "They went up to the city. As they came within the city, behold, Samuel came out towards them, to go up to the high place.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 9:15"}, "Now the LORD had revealed to Samuel a day before Saul came, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 9:16"}, "\u201cTomorrow about this time I will send you a man out of the land of Benjamin, and you shall anoint him to be prince over\nmy people Israel. He will save my people out of the hand of the Philistines; for I have looked upon my people, because their\ncry has come to me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 9:17"}, "When Samuel saw Saul, the LORD said to him, \u201cBehold, the man of whom I spoke to you! He will have authority over my\npeople.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 9:18"}, "Then Saul approached Samuel in the gateway, and said, \u201cPlease tell me where the seer\u2019s house is.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 9:19"}, "Samuel answered Saul, and said, \u201cI am the seer. Go up before me to the high place, for you are to eat with me today. In\nthe morning I will let you go, and will tell you all that is in your heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 9:20"}, "As for your donkeys who were lost three days ago, don\u2019t set your mind on them; for they have been found. For whom is all\nthat is desirable in Israel? Is it not for you, and for all your father\u2019s house?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 9:21"}, "Saul answered, \u201cAm I not a Benjamite, of the smallest of the tribes of Israel? And my family the least of all the\nfamilies of the tribe of Benjamin? Why then do you speak to me like this?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 9:22"}, "Samuel took Saul and his servant, and brought them into the guest room, and made them sit in the best place amongst those\nwho were invited, who were about thirty persons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 9:23"}, "Samuel said to the cook, \u201cBring the portion which I gave you, of which I said to you, \u2018Set it aside.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 9:24"}, "The cook took up the thigh, and that which was on it, and set it before Saul. Samuel said, \u201cBehold, that which has been\nreserved! Set it before yourself and eat; because it has been kept for you for the appointed time, for I said, \u2018I have invited\nthe people.\u2019\u201d So Saul ate with Samuel that day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 9:25"}, "When they had come down from the high place into the city, he talked with Saul on the housetop.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 9:26"}, "They arose early; and about daybreak, Samuel called to Saul on the housetop, saying, \u201cGet up, that I may send you away.\u201d\nSaul arose, and they both went outside, he and Samuel, together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 9:27"}, "As they were going down at the end of the city, Samuel said to Saul, \u201cTell the servant to go on ahead of us.\u201d He went\nahead, then Samuel said, \u201cBut stand still first, that I may cause you to hear Allah\u2019s message.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 10:1"}, "Then Samuel took the vial of oil, and poured it on his head, and kissed him, and said, \u201cHasn\u2019t the LORD anointed you to be\nprince over his inheritance? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 10:2"}, "When you have departed from me today, then you will find two men by Rachel\u2019s tomb, on the border of Benjamin at Zelzah.\nThey will tell you, \u2018The donkeys which you went to look for have been found; and behold, your father has stopped caring about\nthe donkeys, and is anxious for you, saying, \u201cWhat shall I do for my son?\u201d\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 10:3"}, "\u201cThen you will go on forward from there, and you will come to the oak of Tabor. Three men will meet you there going up to\nAllah to Bethel, one carrying three young goats, and another carrying three loaves of bread, and another carrying a container\nof wine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 10:4"}, "They will greet you, and give you two loaves of bread, which you shall receive from their hand.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 10:5"}, "\u201cAfter that you will come to the hill of Allah, where the garrison of the Philistines is; and it will happen, when you\nhave come there to the city, that you will meet a band of prophets coming down from the high place with a lute, a tambourine, a\npipe, and a harp before them; and they will be prophesying. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 10:6"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s Spirit will come mightily on you, and you will prophesy with them, and will be turned into another man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 10:7"}, "Let it be, when these signs have come to you, that you do what is appropriate for the occasion; for Allah is with you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 10:8"}, "\u201cGo down ahead of me to Gilgal; and behold, I will come down to you, to offer burnt offerings, and to sacrifice sacrifices\nof peace offerings. Wait seven days, until I come to you, and show you what you are to do.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 10:9"}, "It was so, that when he had turned his back to go from Samuel, Allah gave him another heart; and all those signs happened\nthat day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 10:10"}, "When they came there to the hill, behold, a band of prophets met him; and the Spirit of Allah came mightily on him, and\nhe prophesied amongst them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 10:11"}, "When all who knew him before saw that, behold, he prophesied with the prophets, then the people said to one another,\n\u201cWhat is this that has come to the son of Kish? Is Saul also amongst the prophets?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 10:12"}, "One of the same place answered, \u201cWho is their father?\u201d Therefore it became a proverb, \u201cIs Saul also amongst the\nprophets?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 10:13"}, "When he had finished prophesying, he came to the high place.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 10:14"}, "Saul\u2019s uncle said to him and to his servant, \u201cWhere did you go?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cTo seek the donkeys. When we saw that they were not found, we came to Samuel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 10:15"}, "Saul\u2019s uncle said, \u201cPlease tell me what Samuel said to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 10:16"}, "Saul said to his uncle, \u201cHe told us plainly that the donkeys were found.\u201d But concerning the matter of the kingdom, of\nwhich Samuel spoke, he didn\u2019t tell him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 10:17"}, "Samuel called the people together to the LORD to Mizpah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 10:18"}, "and he said to the children of Israel, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of Israel, says \u2018I brought Israel up out of Egypt, and I\ndelivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians, and out of the hand of all the kingdoms that oppressed you.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 10:19"}, "But you have today rejected your Allah, who himself saves you out of all your calamities and your distresses; and you\nhave said to him, \u2018No! Set a king over us.\u2019 Now therefore present yourselves before the LORD by your tribes, and by your\nthousands.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 10:20"}, "So Samuel brought all the tribes of Israel near, and the tribe of Benjamin was chosen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 10:21"}, "He brought the tribe of Benjamin near by their families; and the family of the Matrites was chosen. Then Saul the son of\nKish was chosen; but when they looked for him, he could not be found.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 10:22"}, "Therefore they asked of the LORD further, \u201cIs there yet a man to come here?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD answered, \u201cBehold, he has hidden himself amongst the baggage.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 10:23"}, "They ran and got him there. When he stood amongst the people, he was higher than any of the people from his shoulders and\nupward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 10:24"}, "Samuel said to all the people, \u201cDo you see him whom the LORD has chosen, that there is no one like him amongst all the\npeople?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shouted, and said, \u201cLong live the king!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 10:25"}, "Then Samuel told the people the regulations of the kingdom, and wrote it in a book, and laid it up before the LORD.\nSamuel sent all the people away, every man to his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 10:26"}, "Saul also went to his house to Gibeah; and the army went with him, whose hearts Allah had touched.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 10:27"}, "But certain worthless fellows said, \u201cHow could this man save us?\u201d They despised him, and brought him no present. But he\nheld his peace. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 11:1"}, "Then Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabesh Gilead: and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201cMake a\ncovenant with us, and we will serve you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 11:2"}, "Nahash the Ammonite said to them, \u201cOn this condition I will make it with you, that all your right eyes be gouged out. I\nwill make this dishonour all Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 11:3"}, "The elders of Jabesh said to him, \u201cGive us seven days, that we may send messengers to all the borders of Israel; and then,\nif there is no one to save us, we will come out to you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 11:4"}, "Then the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul, and spoke these words in the ears of the people, then all the people lifted up\ntheir voice, and wept. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 11:5"}, "Behold, Saul came following the oxen out of the field; and Saul said, \u201cWhat ails the people that they weep?\u201d They told him\nthe words of the men of Jabesh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 11:6"}, "Allah\u2019s Spirit came mightily on Saul when he heard those words, and his anger burnt hot.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 11:7"}, "He took a yoke of oxen, and cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the borders of Israel by the hand of\nmessengers, saying, \u201cWhoever doesn\u2019t come out after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done to his oxen.\u201d The dread of the\nLORD fell on the people, and they came out as one man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 11:8"}, "He counted them in Bezek; and the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 11:9"}, "They said to the messengers who came, \u201cTell the men of Jabesh Gilead, \u2018Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot, you will be\nrescued.\u2019\u201d The messengers came and told the men of Jabesh; and they were glad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 11:10"}, "Therefore the men of Jabesh said, \u201cTomorrow we will come out to you, and you shall do with us all that seems good to\nyou.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 11:11"}, "On the next day, Saul put the people in three companies; and they came into the middle of the camp in the morning watch,\nand struck the Ammonites until the heat of the day. Those who remained were scattered, so that no two of them were left\ntogether. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 11:12"}, "The people said to Samuel, \u201cWho is he who said, \u2018Shall Saul reign over us?\u2019 Bring those men, that we may put them to\ndeath!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 11:13"}, "Saul said, \u201cNo man shall be put to death today; for today the LORD has rescued Israel.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 11:14"}, "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s go to Gilgal, and renew the kingdom there.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 11:15"}, "All the people went to Gilgal; and there they made Saul king before the LORD in Gilgal. There they offered sacrifices of\npeace offerings before the LORD; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 12:1"}, "Samuel said to all Israel, \u201cBehold, I have listened to your voice in all that you said to me, and have made a king over\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 12:2"}, "Now, behold, the king walks before you. I am old and grey-headed. Behold, my sons are with you. I have walked before you\nfrom my youth to this day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 12:3"}, "Here I am. Witness against me before the LORD, and before his anointed. Whose ox have I taken? Whose donkey have I taken?\nWhom have I defrauded? Whom have I oppressed? Of whose hand have I taken a bribe to make me blind my eyes? I will restore it to\nyou.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 12:4"}, "They said, \u201cYou have not defrauded us, nor oppressed us, neither have you taken anything from anyone\u2019s hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 12:5"}, "He said to them, \u201cThe LORD is witness against you, and his anointed is witness today, that you have not found anything in\nmy hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cHe is witness.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 12:6"}, "Samuel said to the people, \u201cIt is the LORD who appointed Musa and Harun, and that brought your fathers up out of the land\nof Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 12:7"}, "Now therefore stand still, that I may plead with you before the LORD concerning all the righteous acts of the LORD, which\nhe did to you and to your fathers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 12:8"}, "\u201cWhen Yaqub had come into Egypt, and your fathers cried to the LORD, then the LORD sent Musa and Harun, who brought your\nfathers out of Egypt, and made them to dwell in this place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 12:9"}, "\u201cBut they forgot the LORD their Allah; and he sold them into the hand of Sisera, captain of the army of Hazor, and into\nthe hand of the Philistines, and into the hand of the king of Moab; and they fought against them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 12:10"}, "They cried to the LORD, and said, \u2018We have sinned, because we have forsaken the LORD, and have served the Baals and the\nAshtaroth: but now deliver us out of the hand of our enemies, and we will serve you.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 12:11"}, "The LORD sent Jerubbaal, Bedan, Jephthah, and Samuel, and delivered you out of the hand of your enemies on every side;\nand you lived in safety. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 12:12"}, "\u201cWhen you saw that Nahash the king of the children of Ammon came against you, you said to me, \u2018No, but a king shall reign\nover us;\u2019 when Allah your LORD was your king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 12:13"}, "Now therefore see the king whom you have chosen, and whom you have asked for. Behold, the LORD has set a king over you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 12:14"}, "If you will fear the LORD, and serve him, and listen to his voice, and not rebel against the commandment of the LORD,\nthen both you and also the king who reigns over you are followers of Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 12:15"}, "But if you will not listen to the LORD\u2019s voice, but rebel against the commandment of the LORD, then the LORD\u2019s hand will\nbe against you, as it was against your fathers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 12:16"}, "\u201cNow therefore stand still and see this great thing, which the LORD will do before your eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 12:17"}, "Isn\u2019t it wheat harvest today? I will call to the LORD, that he may send thunder and rain; and you will know and see that\nyour wickedness is great, which you have done in the LORD\u2019s sight, in asking for a king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 12:18"}, "So Samuel called to the LORD; and the LORD sent thunder and rain that day. Then all the people greatly feared the LORD\nand Samuel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 12:19"}, "All the people said to Samuel, \u201cPray for your servants to Allah your LORD, that we not die; for we have added to all our\nsins this evil, to ask for a king.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 12:20"}, "Samuel said to the people, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid. You have indeed done all this evil; yet don\u2019t turn away from following the\nLORD, but serve the LORD with all your heart. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 12:21"}, "Don\u2019t turn away to go after vain things which can\u2019t profit or deliver, for they are vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 12:22"}, "For the LORD will not forsake his people for his great name\u2019s sake, because it has pleased the LORD to make you a people\nfor himself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 12:23"}, "Moreover as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against the LORD in ceasing to pray for you: but I will instruct\nyou in the good and the right way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 12:24"}, "Only fear the LORD, and serve him in truth with all your heart; for consider what great things he has done for you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 12:25"}, "But if you keep doing evil, you will be consumed, both you and your king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 13:1"}, "Saul was thirty years old when he became king, and he reigned over Israel forty-two\nyears.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The traditional Hebrew text omits \u201cthirty\u201d and \u201cforty-\u201d. The blanks are filled in here from a few\nmanuscripts of the Septuagint."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 13:2"}, "Saul chose for himself three thousand men of Israel, of which two thousand were with Saul in Michmash and in the Mount of\nBethel, and one thousand were with Jonathan in Gibeah of Benjamin. He sent the rest of the people to their own tents.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 13:3"}, "Jonathan struck the garrison of the Philistines that was in Geba, and the Philistines heard of it. Saul blew the trumpet\nthroughout all the land, saying, \u201cLet the Hebrews hear!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 13:4"}, "All Israel heard that Saul had struck the garrison of the Philistines, and also that Israel was considered an abomination\nto the Philistines. The people were gathered together after Saul to Gilgal.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 13:5"}, "The Philistines assembled themselves together to fight with Israel, thirty thousand chariots, and six thousand horsemen,\nand people as the sand which is on the seashore in multitude. They came up and encamped in Michmash, eastward of Beth Aven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 13:6"}, "When the men of Israel saw that they were in trouble (for the people were distressed), then the people hid themselves in\ncaves, in thickets, in rocks, in tombs, and in pits. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 13:7"}, "Now some of the Hebrews had gone over the Jordan to the land of Gad and Gilead; but as for Saul, he was yet in Gilgal, and\nall the people followed him trembling. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 13:8"}, "He stayed seven days, according to the time set by Samuel; but Samuel didn\u2019t come to Gilgal, and the people were\nscattering from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 13:9"}, "Saul said, \u201cBring the burnt offering to me here, and the peace offerings.\u201d He offered the burnt offering.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 13:10"}, "It came to pass that as soon as he had finished offering the burnt offering, behold, Samuel came; and Saul went out to\nmeet him, that he might greet him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 13:11"}, "Samuel said, \u201cWhat have you done?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Saul said, \u201cBecause I saw that the people were scattered from me, and that you didn\u2019t come within the days appointed, and\nthat the Philistines assembled themselves together at Michmash; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 13:12"}, "therefore I said, \u2018Now the Philistines will come down on me to Gilgal, and I haven\u2019t entreated the favour of the LORD.\u2019 I\nforced myself therefore, and offered the burnt offering.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 13:13"}, "Samuel said to Saul, \u201cYou have done foolishly. You have not kept the commandment of Allah your LORD, which he commanded\nyou; for now the LORD would have established your kingdom on Israel forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 13:14"}, "But now your kingdom will not continue. The LORD has sought for himself a man after his own heart, and the LORD has\nappointed him to be prince over his people, because you have not kept that which the LORD commanded you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 13:15"}, "Samuel arose, and went from Gilgal to Gibeah of Benjamin. Saul counted the people who were present with him, about six\nhundred men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 13:16"}, "Saul, and Jonathan his son, and the people who were present with them, stayed in Geba of Benjamin; but the Philistines\nencamped in Michmash. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 13:17"}, "The raiders came out of the camp of the Philistines in three companies: one company turned to the way that leads to\nOphrah, to the land of Shual; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 13:18"}, "another company turned the way to Beth Horon; and another company turned the way of the border that looks down on the\nvalley of Zeboim towards the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 13:19"}, "Now there was no blacksmith found throughout all the land of Israel; for the Philistines said, \u201cLest the Hebrews make\nthemselves swords or spears\u201d; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 13:20"}, "but all the Israelites went down to the Philistines, each man to sharpen his own ploughshare, mattock, axe, and sickle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 13:21"}, "The price was one payim", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A payim (or pim) was 2/3 shekel of silver, or 0.26 ounces, or 7.6\ngrams"]}], "caller": "+"}, " each to sharpen mattocks, ploughshares, pitchforks, axes, and goads.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 13:22"}, "So it came to pass in the day of battle, that neither sword nor spear was found in the hand of any of the people who were\nwith Saul and Jonathan; but Saul and Jonathan his son had them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 13:23"}, "The garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass of Michmash.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 14:1"}, "Now it fell on a day, that Jonathan the son of Saul said to the young man who bore his armour, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s go over to the\nPhilistines\u2019 garrison that is on the other side.\u201d But he didn\u2019t tell his father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 14:2"}, "Saul stayed in the uttermost part of Gibeah under the pomegranate tree which is in Migron: and the people who were with\nhim were about six hundred men; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 14:3"}, "including Ahijah, the son of Ahitub, Ichabod\u2019s brother, the son of Phinehas, the son of Eli, the priest of the LORD in\nShiloh, wearing an ephod. The people didn\u2019t know that Jonathan was gone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 14:4"}, "Between the passes, by which Jonathan sought to go over to the Philistines\u2019 garrison, there was a rocky crag on the one\nside, and a rocky crag on the other side: and the name of the one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 14:5"}, "The one crag rose up on the north in front of Michmash, and the other on the south in front of Geba.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 14:6"}, "Jonathan said to the young man who bore his armour, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s go over to the garrison of these uncircumcised. It may be\nthat the LORD will work for us; for there is no restraint on the LORD to save by many or by few.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 14:7"}, "His armour bearer said to him, \u201cDo all that is in your heart. Turn and, behold, I am with you according to your heart.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 14:8"}, "Then Jonathan said, \u201cBehold, we will pass over to the men, and we will reveal ourselves to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 14:9"}, "If they say this to us, \u2018Wait until we come to you!\u2019 then we will stand still in our place, and will not go up to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 14:10"}, "But if they say this, \u2018Come up to us!\u2019 then we will go up; for the LORD has delivered them into our hand. This shall be\nthe sign to us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 14:11"}, "Both of them revealed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines: and the Philistines said, \u201cBehold, the Hebrews are\ncoming out of the holes where they had hidden themselves!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 14:12"}, "The men of the garrison answered Jonathan and his armour bearer, and said, \u201cCome up to us, and we will show you\nsomething!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Jonathan said to his armour bearer, \u201cCome up after me; for the LORD has delivered them into the hand of Israel.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 14:13"}, "Jonathan climbed up on his hands and on his feet, and his armour bearer after him: and they fell before Jonathan; and his\narmour bearer killed them after him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 14:14"}, "That first slaughter, which Jonathan and his armour bearer made, was about twenty men, within as it were half a furrow\u2019s\nlength in an acre of land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 14:15"}, "There was a trembling in the camp, in the field, and amongst all the people; the garrison, and the raiders, also\ntrembled; and the earth quaked, so there was an exceedingly great trembling.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 14:16"}, "The watchmen of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin looked; and behold, the multitude melted away and scattered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 14:17"}, "Then Saul said to the people who were with him, \u201cCount now, and see who is missing from us.\u201d When they had counted,\nbehold, Jonathan and his armour bearer were not there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 14:18"}, "Saul said to Ahijah, \u201cBring Allah\u2019s ark here.\u201d For Allah\u2019s ark was with the children of Israel at that time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 14:19"}, "While Saul talked to the priest, the tumult that was in the camp of the Philistines went on and increased; and Saul said\nto the priest, \u201cWithdraw your hand!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 14:20"}, "Saul and all the people who were with him were gathered together, and came to the battle; and behold, they were all\nstriking each other with their swords in very great confusion. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 14:21"}, "Now the Hebrews who were with the Philistines before, and who went up with them into the camp, from all around, even they\nalso turned to be with the Israelites who were with Saul and Jonathan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 14:22"}, "Likewise all the men of Israel who had hidden themselves in the hill country of Ephraim, when they heard that the\nPhilistines fled, even they also followed hard after them in the battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 14:23"}, "So the LORD saved Israel that day; and the battle passed over by Beth Aven.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 14:24"}, "The men of Israel were distressed that day; for Saul had adjured the people, saying, \u201cCursed is the man who eats any food\nuntil it is evening, and I am avenged of my enemies.\u201d So none of the people tasted food.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 14:25"}, "All the people came into the forest; and there was honey on the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 14:26"}, "When the people had come to the forest, behold, honey was dripping, but no one put his hand to his mouth; for the people\nfeared the oath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 14:27"}, "But Jonathan didn\u2019t hear when his father commanded the people with the oath. Therefore he put out the end of the rod that\nwas in his hand, and dipped it in the honeycomb, and put his hand to his mouth; and his eyes brightened.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 14:28"}, "Then one of the people answered, and said, \u201cYour father directly commanded the people with an oath, saying, \u2018Cursed is\nthe man who eats food today.\u2019\u201d So the people were faint. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 14:29"}, "Then Jonathan said, \u201cMy father has troubled the land. Please look how my eyes have brightened, because I tasted a little\nof this honey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 14:30"}, "How much more, if perhaps the people had eaten freely today of the plunder of their enemies which they found? For now\nthere has been no great slaughter amongst the Philistines.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 14:31"}, "They struck the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon. The people were very faint;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 14:32"}, "and the people pounced on the plunder, and took sheep, cattle, and calves, and killed them on the ground; and the people\nate them with the blood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 14:33"}, "Then they told Saul, saying, \u201cBehold, the people are sinning against the LORD, in that they eat meat with the blood.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cYou have dealt treacherously. Roll a large stone to me today!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 14:34"}, "Saul said, \u201cDisperse yourselves amongst the people, and tell them, \u2018Every man bring me here his ox, and every man his\nsheep, and kill them here, and eat; and don\u2019t sin against the LORD in eating meat with the blood.\u2019\u201d All the people brought\nevery man his ox with him that night, and killed them there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 14:35"}, "Saul built an altar to the LORD. This was the first altar that he built to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1SA 14:36"}, "Saul said, \u201cLet\u2019s go down after the Philistines by night, and take plunder amongst them until the morning light, and\nlet\u2019s not leave a man of them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cDo whatever seems good to you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then the priest said, \u201cLet\u2019s draw near here to Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1SA 14:37"}, "Saul asked counsel of Allah, \u201cShall I go down after the Philistines? Will you deliver them into the hand of Israel?\u201d But\nhe didn\u2019t answer him that day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1SA 14:38"}, "Saul said, \u201cDraw near here, all you chiefs of the people; and know and see in which this sin has been today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1SA 14:39"}, "For, as the LORD lives, who saves Israel, though it is in Jonathan my son, he shall surely die.\u201d But there was not a man\namongst all the people who answered him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1SA 14:40"}, "Then he said to all Israel, \u201cYou be on one side, and I and Jonathan my son will be on the other side.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The people said to Saul, \u201cDo what seems good to you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1SA 14:41"}, "Therefore Saul said to the LORD, Allah of Israel, \u201cShow the right.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Jonathan and Saul were chosen, but the people escaped. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1SA 14:42"}, "Saul said, \u201cCast lots between me and Jonathan my son.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Jonathan was selected. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1SA 14:43"}, "Then Saul said to Jonathan, \u201cTell me what you have done!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Jonathan told him, and said, \u201cI certainly did taste a little honey with the end of the rod that was in my hand; and behold,\nI must die.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1SA 14:44"}, "Saul said, \u201cAllah do so and more also; for you shall surely die, Jonathan.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1SA 14:45"}, "The people said to Saul, \u201cShall Jonathan die, who has worked this great salvation in Israel? Far from it! As the LORD\nlives, there shall not one hair of his head fall to the ground; for he has worked with Allah today!\u201d So the people rescued\nJonathan, that he didn\u2019t die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1SA 14:46"}, "Then Saul went up from following the Philistines; and the Philistines went to their own place.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1SA 14:47"}, "Now when Saul had taken the kingdom over Israel, he fought against all his enemies on every side, against Moab, and\nagainst the children of Ammon, and against Edom, and against the kings of Zobah, and against the Philistines. Wherever he\nturned himself, he defeated them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1SA 14:48"}, "He did valiantly, and struck the Amalekites, and delivered Israel out of the hands of those who plundered them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1SA 14:49"}, "Now the sons of Saul were Jonathan, Ishvi, and Malchishua; and the names of his two daughters were these: the name of the\nfirstborn Merab, and the name of the younger Michal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1SA 14:50"}, "The name of Saul\u2019s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz. The name of the captain of his army was Abner the son of\nNer, Saul\u2019s uncle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1SA 14:51"}, "Kish was the father of Saul; and Ner the father of Abner was the son of Abiel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1SA 14:52"}, "There was severe war against the Philistines all the days of Saul; and when Saul saw any mighty man, or any valiant man,\nhe took him into his service. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 15:1"}, "Samuel said to Saul, \u201cThe LORD sent me to anoint you to be king over his people, over Israel. Now therefore listen to the\nvoice of the LORD\u2019s words. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 15:2"}, "The LORD of Armies says, \u2018I remember what Amalek did to Israel, how he set himself against him on the way, when he came up\nout of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 15:3"}, "Now go and strike Amalek, and utterly destroy all that they have, and don\u2019t spare them; but kill both man and woman,\ninfant and nursing baby, ox and sheep, camel and donkey.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 15:4"}, "Saul summoned the people, and counted them in Telaim, two hundred thousand footmen, and ten thousand men of Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 15:5"}, "Saul came to the city of Amalek, and set an ambush in the valley.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 15:6"}, "Saul said to the Kenites, \u201cGo, depart, go down from amongst the Amalekites, lest I destroy you with them; for you showed\nkindness to all the children of Israel, when they came up out of Egypt.\u201d So the Kenites departed from amongst the Amalekites.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 15:7"}, "Saul struck the Amalekites, from Havilah as you go to Shur, that is before Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 15:8"}, "He took Agag the king of the Amalekites alive, and utterly destroyed all the people with the edge of the sword.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 15:9"}, "But Saul and the people spared Agag, and the best of the sheep, of the cattle, and of the fat calves, and the lambs, and\nall that was good, and were not willing to utterly destroy them; but everything that was vile and refuse, that they destroyed\nutterly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 15:10"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s word came to Samuel, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 15:11"}, "\u201cIt grieves me that I have set up Saul to be king; for he has turned back from following me, and has not performed my\ncommandments.\u201d Samuel was angry; and he cried to the LORD all night.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 15:12"}, "Samuel rose early to meet Saul in the morning; and Samuel was told, saying, \u201cSaul came to Carmel, and behold, he set up a\nmonument for himself, and turned, and passed on, and went down to Gilgal.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 15:13"}, "Samuel came to Saul; and Saul said to him, \u201cYou are blessed by the LORD! I have performed the commandment of the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 15:14"}, "Samuel said, \u201cThen what does this bleating of the sheep in my ears, and the lowing of the cattle which I hear mean?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 15:15"}, "Saul said, \u201cThey have brought them from the Amalekites; for the people spared the best of the sheep and of the cattle, to\nsacrifice to Allah your LORD. We have utterly destroyed the rest.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 15:16"}, "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201cStay, and I will tell you what the LORD said to me last night.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cSay on.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 15:17"}, "Samuel said, \u201cThough you were little in your own sight, weren\u2019t you made the head of the tribes of Israel? The LORD\nanointed you king over Israel; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 15:18"}, "and the LORD sent you on a journey, and said, \u2018Go, and utterly destroy the sinners the Amalekites, and fight against them\nuntil they are consumed.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 15:19"}, "Why then didn\u2019t you obey the LORD\u2019s voice, but took the plunder, and did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 15:20"}, "Saul said to Samuel, \u201cBut I have obeyed the LORD\u2019s voice, and have gone the way which the LORD sent me, and have brought\nAgag the king of Amalek, and have utterly destroyed the Amalekites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 15:21"}, "But the people took of the plunder, sheep and cattle, the chief of the devoted things, to sacrifice to Allah your LORD in\nGilgal.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 15:22"}, "Samuel said, \u201cHas the LORD as great delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices, as in obeying the LORD\u2019s voice? Behold, to\nobey is better than sacrifice, and to listen than the fat of rams.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 15:23"}, "For rebellion is as the sin of witchcraft, and stubbornness is as idolatry and\nteraphim.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with inheritance rights to the\nhousehold property."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Because you have rejected the LORD\u2019s word, he has also rejected you from being king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 15:24"}, "Saul said to Samuel, \u201cI have sinned; for I have transgressed the commandment of the LORD, and your words, because I\nfeared the people, and obeyed their voice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 15:25"}, "Now therefore, please pardon my sin, and turn again with me, that I may worship the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 15:26"}, "Samuel said to Saul, \u201cI will not return with you; for you have rejected the LORD\u2019s word, and the LORD has rejected you\nfrom being king over Israel.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 15:27"}, "As Samuel turned around to go away, Saul grabbed the skirt of his robe, and it tore.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 15:28"}, "Samuel said to him, \u201cThe LORD has torn the kingdom of Israel from you today, and has given it to a neighbour of yours who\nis better than you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 15:29"}, "Also the Strength of Israel will not lie nor repent; for he is not a man, that he should repent.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 15:30"}, "Then he said, \u201cI have sinned; yet please honour me now before the elders of my people, and before Israel, and come back\nwith me, that I may worship Allah your LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 15:31"}, "So Samuel went back with Saul; and Saul worshipped the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 15:32"}, "Then Samuel said, \u201cBring Agag the king of the Amalekites here to me!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Agag came to him cheerfully. Agag said, \u201cSurely the bitterness of death is past.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 15:33"}, "Samuel said, \u201cAs your sword has made women childless, so your mother will be childless amongst women!\u201d Then Samuel cut\nAgag in pieces before the LORD in Gilgal. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 15:34"}, "Then Samuel went to Ramah; and Saul went up to his house to Gibeah of Saul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 15:35"}, "Samuel came no more to see Saul until the day of his death; for Samuel mourned for Saul: and the LORD grieved that he had\nmade Saul king over Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 16:1"}, "The LORD said to Samuel, \u201cHow long will you mourn for Saul, since I have rejected him from being king over Israel? Fill\nyour horn with oil, and go. I will send you to Jesse the Bethlehemite; for I have provided a king for myself amongst his sons.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 16:2"}, "Samuel said, \u201cHow can I go? If Saul hears it, he will kill me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cTake a heifer with you, and say, I have come to sacrifice to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 16:3"}, "Call Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show you what you shall do. You shall anoint to me him whom I name to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 16:4"}, "Samuel did that which the LORD spoke, and came to Bethlehem. The elders of the city came to meet him trembling, and said,\n\u201cDo you come peaceably?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 16:5"}, "He said, \u201cPeaceably; I have come to sacrifice to the LORD. Sanctify yourselves, and come with me to the sacrifice.\u201d He\nsanctified Jesse and his sons, and called them to the sacrifice.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 16:6"}, "When they had come, he looked at Eliab, and said, \u201cSurely the LORD\u2019s anointed is before him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 16:7"}, "But the LORD said to Samuel, \u201cDon\u2019t look on his face, or on the height of his stature, because I have rejected him; for I\ndon\u2019t see as man sees. For man looks at the outward appearance, but the LORD looks at the heart.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 16:8"}, "Then Jesse called Abinadab, and made him pass before Samuel. He said, \u201cThe LORD has not chosen this one, either.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 16:9"}, "Then Jesse made Shammah to pass by. He said, \u201cThe LORD has not chosen this one, either.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 16:10"}, "Jesse made seven of his sons to pass before Samuel. Samuel said to Jesse, \u201cThe LORD has not chosen these.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 16:11"}, "Samuel said to Jesse, \u201cAre all your children here?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cThere remains yet the youngest. Behold, he is keeping the sheep.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samuel said to Jesse, \u201cSend and get him, for we will not sit down until he comes here.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 16:12"}, "He sent, and brought him in. Now he was ruddy, with a handsome face and good appearance. The LORD said, \u201cArise! Anoint\nhim, for this is he.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 16:13"}, "Then Samuel took the horn of oil, and anointed him in the middle of his brothers. Then the LORD\u2019s Spirit came mightily on\nDawood from that day forward. So Samuel rose up and went to Ramah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 16:14"}, "Now the LORD\u2019s Spirit departed from Saul, and an evil spirit from the LORD troubled him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 16:15"}, "Saul\u2019s servants said to him, \u201cSee now, an evil spirit from Allah troubles you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 16:16"}, "Let our lord now command your servants who are in front of you to seek out a man who is a skilful player on the harp.\nThen when the evil spirit from Allah is on you, he will play with his hand, and you will be well.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 16:17"}, "Saul said to his servants, \u201cProvide me now a man who can play well, and bring him to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 16:18"}, "Then one of the young men answered, and said, \u201cBehold, I have seen a son of Jesse the Bethlehemite who is skilful in\nplaying, a mighty man of valour, a man of war, prudent in speech, and a handsome person; and the LORD is with him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 16:19"}, "Therefore Saul sent messengers to Jesse, and said, \u201cSend me Dawood your son, who is with the sheep.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 16:20"}, "Jesse took a donkey loaded with bread, and a container of wine, and a young goat, and sent them by Dawood his son to\nSaul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 16:21"}, "Dawood came to Saul, and stood before him. He loved him greatly; and he became his armour bearer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 16:22"}, "Saul sent to Jesse, saying, \u201cPlease let Dawood stand before me; for he has found favour in my sight.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 16:23"}, "When the spirit from Allah was on Saul, Dawood took the harp, and played with his hand; so Saul was refreshed, and was\nwell, and the evil spirit departed from him. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 17:1"}, "Now the Philistines gathered together their armies to battle; and they were gathered together at Socoh, which belongs to\nJudah, and encamped between Socoh and Azekah, in Ephesdammim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 17:2"}, "Saul and the men of Israel were gathered together, and encamped in the valley of Elah, and set the battle in array against\nthe Philistines. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 17:3"}, "The Philistines stood on the mountain on the one side, and Israel stood on the mountain on the other side: and there was a\nvalley between them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 17:4"}, "A champion out of the camp of the Philistines named Goliath, of Gath, whose height was six cubits and a\nspan", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18 inches\nor 46 centimetres. A span is the length from the tip of a man\u2019s thumb to the tip of his little finger when his hand is\nstretched out (about half a cubit, or 9 inches, or 22.8 cm.) Therefore, Goliath was about 9 feet and 9 inches or 2.97 metres\ntall."]}], "caller": "+"}, " went out. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 17:5"}, "He had a helmet of bronze on his head, and he wore a coat of mail; and the weight of the coat was five thousand\nshekels", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 5000 shekels is about 50 kilograms or 110\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of bronze. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 17:6"}, "He had bronze shin armour on his legs, and a bronze javelin between his shoulders.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 17:7"}, "The staff of his spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam; and his spear\u2019s head weighed six hundred shekels of\niron.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 600 shekels is about 6 kilograms or about 13\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " His shield bearer went before him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 17:8"}, "He stood and cried to the armies of Israel, and said to them, \u201cWhy have you come out to set your battle in array? Am I not\na Philistine, and you servants to Saul? Choose a man for yourselves, and let him come down to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 17:9"}, "If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then will we be your servants; but if I prevail against him and kill him, then\nyou will be our servants and serve us.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 17:10"}, "The Philistine said, \u201cI defy the armies of Israel today! Give me a man, that we may fight together!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 17:11"}, "When Saul and all Israel heard those words of the Philistine, they were dismayed, and greatly afraid.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 17:12"}, "Now Dawood was the son of that Ephrathite of Bethlehem Judah, whose name was Jesse; and he had eight sons. The man was an\nelderly old man in the days of Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 17:13"}, "The three oldest sons of Jesse had gone after Saul to the battle: and the names of his three sons who went to the battle\nwere Eliab the firstborn, and next to him Abinadab, and the third Shammah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 17:14"}, "Dawood was the youngest; and the three oldest followed Saul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 17:15"}, "Now Dawood went back and forth from Saul to feed his father\u2019s sheep at Bethlehem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 17:16"}, "The Philistine came near morning and evening, and presented himself forty days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 17:17"}, "Jesse said to Dawood his son, \u201cNow take for your brothers an ephah\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of this parched grain, and these ten loaves, and carry them quickly to the camp to your brothers;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 17:18"}, "and bring these ten cheeses to the captain of their thousand, and see how your brothers are doing, and bring back news.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 17:19"}, "Now Saul, and they, and all the men of Israel, were in the valley of Elah, fighting with the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 17:20"}, "Dawood rose up early in the morning, and left the sheep with a keeper, and took and went, as Jesse had commanded him. He\ncame to the place of the wagons, as the army which was going out to the fight shouted for the battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 17:21"}, "Israel and the Philistines put the battle in array, army against army.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 17:22"}, "Dawood left his baggage in the hand of the keeper of the baggage, and ran to the army, and came and greeted his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 17:23"}, "As he talked with them, behold, the champion, the Philistine of Gath, Goliath by name, came up out of the ranks of the\nPhilistines, and said the same words; and Dawood heard them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 17:24"}, "All the men of Israel, when they saw the man, fled from him, and were terrified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 17:25"}, "The men of Israel said, \u201cHave you seen this man who has come up? He has surely come up to defy Israel. The king will give\ngreat riches to the man who kills him, and will give him his daughter, and make his father\u2019s house free in Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 17:26"}, "Dawood spoke to the men who stood by him, saying, \u201cWhat shall be done to the man who kills this Philistine, and takes\naway the reproach from Israel? For who is this uncircumcised Philistine, that he should defy the armies of the living Allah?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 17:27"}, "The people answered him in this way, saying, \u201cSo shall it be done to the man who kills him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 17:28"}, "Eliab his oldest brother heard when he spoke to the men; and Eliab\u2019s anger burnt against Dawood, and he said, \u201cWhy have\nyou come down? With whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness? I know your pride, and the naughtiness of your heart;\nfor you have come down that you might see the battle.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 17:29"}, "Dawood said, \u201cWhat have I now done? Is there not a cause?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 17:30"}, "He turned away from him towards another, and spoke like that again; and the people answered him again the same way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 17:31"}, "When the words were heard which Dawood spoke, they rehearsed them before Saul; and he sent for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 17:32"}, "Dawood said to Saul, \u201cLet no man\u2019s heart fail because of him. Your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 17:33"}, "Saul said to Dawood, \u201cYou are not able to go against this Philistine to fight with him; for you are but a youth, and he a\nman of war from his youth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 17:34"}, "Dawood said to Saul, \u201cYour servant was keeping his father\u2019s sheep; and when a lion or a bear came, and took a lamb out of\nthe flock, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 17:35"}, "I went out after him, and struck him, and rescued it out of his mouth. When he arose against me, I caught him by his\nbeard, and struck him, and killed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1SA 17:36"}, "Your servant struck both the lion and the bear. This uncircumcised Philistine shall be as one of them, since he has\ndefied the armies of the living Allah.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1SA 17:37"}, "Dawood said, \u201cThe LORD who delivered me out of the paw of the lion, and out of the paw of the bear, he will deliver me\nout of the hand of this Philistine.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Saul said to Dawood, \u201cGo! The LORD will be with you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1SA 17:38"}, "Saul dressed Dawood with his clothing. He put a helmet of bronze on his head, and he clad him with a coat of mail.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1SA 17:39"}, "Dawood strapped his sword on his clothing, and he tried to move; for he had not tested it. Dawood said to Saul, \u201cI can\u2019t\ngo with these; for I have not tested them.\u201d Then Dawood took them off.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1SA 17:40"}, "He took his staff in his hand, and chose for himself five smooth stones out of the brook, and put them in the pouch of\nhis shepherd\u2019s bag which he had. His sling was in his hand; and he came near to the Philistine.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1SA 17:41"}, "The Philistine walked and came near to Dawood; and the man who bore the shield went before him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1SA 17:42"}, "When the Philistine looked around, and saw Dawood, he disdained him; for he was but a youth, and ruddy, and had a good\nlooking face. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1SA 17:43"}, "The Philistine said to Dawood, \u201cAm I a dog, that you come to me with sticks?\u201d The Philistine cursed Dawood by his gods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1SA 17:44"}, "The Philistine said to Dawood, \u201cCome to me, and I will give your flesh to the birds of the sky, and to the animals of the\nfield.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1SA 17:45"}, "Then Dawood said to the Philistine, \u201cYou come to me with a sword, with a spear, and with a javelin; but I come to you in\nthe name of the LORD of Armies, Allah of the armies of Israel, whom you have defied.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1SA 17:46"}, "Today, the LORD will deliver you into my hand. I will strike you, and take your head from off you. I will give the dead\nbodies of the army of the Philistines today to the birds of the sky, and to the wild animals of the earth; that all the earth\nmay know that there is Allah in Israel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1SA 17:47"}, "and that all this assembly may know that the LORD doesn\u2019t save with sword and spear; for the battle is the LORD\u2019s, and he\nwill give you into our hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1SA 17:48"}, "When the Philistine arose, and walked and came near to meet Dawood, Dawood hurried, and ran towards the army to meet the\nPhilistine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1SA 17:49"}, "Dawood put his hand in his bag, took a stone, and slung it, and struck the Philistine in his forehead. The stone sank\ninto his forehead, and he fell on his face to the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1SA 17:50"}, "So Dawood prevailed over the Philistine with a sling and with a stone, and struck the Philistine, and killed him; but\nthere was no sword in the hand of Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1SA 17:51"}, "Then Dawood ran, stood over the Philistine, took his sword, drew it out of its sheath, killed him, and cut off his head\nwith it. When the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1SA 17:52"}, "The men of Israel and of Judah arose and shouted, and pursued the Philistines as far as Gai and to the gates of Ekron.\nThe wounded of the Philistines fell down by the way to Shaaraim, even to Gath and to Ekron.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "1SA 17:53"}, "The children of Israel returned from chasing after the Philistines and they plundered their camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "1SA 17:54"}, "Dawood took the head of the Philistine, and brought it to Jerusalem; but he put his armour in his tent.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "1SA 17:55"}, "When Saul saw Dawood go out against the Philistine, he said to Abner, the captain of the army, \u201cAbner, whose son is this\nyouth?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Abner said, \u201cAs your soul lives, O king, I can\u2019t tell.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "1SA 17:56"}, "The king said, \u201cEnquire whose son the young man is!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "1SA 17:57"}, "As Dawood returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, Abner took him and brought him before Saul with the head of the\nPhilistine in his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "1SA 17:58"}, "Saul said to him, \u201cWhose son are you, you young man?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood answered, \u201cI am the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 18:1"}, "When he had finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan was knit with the soul of Dawood, and Jonathan loved him as\nhis own soul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 18:2"}, "Saul took him that day, and wouldn\u2019t let him go home to his father\u2019s house any more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 18:3"}, "Then Jonathan and Dawood made a covenant, because he loved him as his own soul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 18:4"}, "Jonathan stripped himself of the robe that was on him, and gave it to Dawood, and his clothing, even including his sword,\nhis bow, and his sash. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 18:5"}, "Dawood went out wherever Saul sent him, and behaved himself wisely; and Saul set him over the men of war. It was good in\nthe sight of all the people, and also in the sight of Saul\u2019s servants.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 18:6"}, "As they came, when Dawood returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, the women came out of all the cities of Israel,\nsinging and dancing, to meet king Saul, with tambourines, with joy, and with instruments of music.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 18:7"}, "The women sang to one another as they played, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cSaul has slain his thousands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Dawood his ten thousands.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 18:8"}, "Saul was very angry, and this saying displeased him. He said, \u201cThey have creditd Dawood with ten thousands, and they have\nonly credited me with thousands. What can he have more but the kingdom?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 18:9"}, "Saul watched Dawood from that day and forward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 18:10"}, "On the next day, an evil spirit from Allah came mightily on Saul, and he prophesied in the middle of the house. Dawood\nplayed with his hand, as he did day by day. Saul had his spear in his hand;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 18:11"}, "and Saul threw the spear, for he said, \u201cI will pin Dawood to the wall!\u201d Dawood escaped from his presence twice.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 18:12"}, "Saul was afraid of Dawood, because the LORD was with him, and had departed from Saul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 18:13"}, "Therefore Saul removed him from his presence, and made him his captain over a thousand; and he went out and came in\nbefore the people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 18:14"}, "Dawood behaved himself wisely in all his ways; and the LORD was with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 18:15"}, "When Saul saw that he behaved himself very wisely, he stood in awe of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 18:16"}, "But all Israel and Judah loved Dawood; for he went out and came in before them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 18:17"}, "Saul said to Dawood, \u201cBehold, my elder daughter Merab, I will give her to you as wife. Only be valiant for me, and fight\nthe LORD\u2019s battles.\u201d For Saul said, \u201cDon\u2019t let my hand be on him, but let the hand of the Philistines be on him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 18:18"}, "Dawood said to Saul, \u201cWho am I, and what is my life, or my father\u2019s family in Israel, that I should be son-in-law to the\nking?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 18:19"}, "But at the time when Merab, Saul\u2019s daughter, should have been given to Dawood, she was given to Adriel the Meholathite as\nwife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 18:20"}, "Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, loved Dawood; and they told Saul, and the thing pleased him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 18:21"}, "Saul said, I will give her to him, that she may be a snare to him, and that the hand of the Philistines may be against\nhim. Therefore Saul said to Dawood, \u201cYou shall today be my son-in-law a second time.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 18:22"}, "Saul commanded his servants, \u201cTalk with Dawood secretly, and say, \u2018Behold, the king has delight in you, and all his\nservants love you. Now therefore be the king\u2019s son-in-law.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 18:23"}, "Saul\u2019s servants spoke those words in the ears of Dawood. Dawood said, \u201cDoes it seem to you a light thing to be the king\u2019s\nson-in-law, since I am a poor man, and little known?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 18:24"}, "The servants of Saul told him, saying, \u201cDawood spoke like this.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 18:25"}, "Saul said, \u201cTell Dawood, \u2018The king desires no dowry except one hundred foreskins of the Philistines, to be avenged of the\nking\u2019s enemies.\u2019\u201d Now Saul thought he would make Dawood fall by the hand of the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 18:26"}, "When his servants told Dawood these words, it pleased Dawood well to be the king\u2019s son-in-law. Before the deadline,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 18:27"}, "Dawood arose and went, he and his men, and killed two hundred men of the Philistines. Then Dawood brought their\nforeskins, and they gave them in full number to the king, that he might be the king\u2019s son-in-law. Then Saul gave him Michal his\ndaughter as wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 18:28"}, "Saul saw and knew that the LORD was with Dawood; and Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, loved him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 18:29"}, "Saul was even more afraid of Dawood; and Saul was Dawood\u2019s enemy continually.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 18:30"}, "Then the princes of the Philistines went out; and as often as they went out, Dawood behaved himself more wisely than all\nthe servants of Saul, so that his name was highly esteemed. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 19:1"}, "Saul spoke to Jonathan his son, and to all his servants, that they should kill Dawood. But Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, greatly\ndelighted in Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 19:2"}, "Jonathan told Dawood, saying, \u201cSaul my father seeks to kill you. Now therefore, please take care of yourself in the\nmorning, and live in a secret place, and hide yourself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 19:3"}, "I will go out and stand beside my father in the field where you are, and I will talk with my father about you; and if I\nsee anything, I will tell you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 19:4"}, "Jonathan spoke good of Dawood to Saul his father, and said to him, \u201cDon\u2019t let the king sin against his servant, against\nDawood; because he has not sinned against you, and because his works have been very good towards you;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 19:5"}, "for he put his life in his hand, and struck the Philistine, and the LORD worked a great victory for all Israel. You saw\nit, and rejoiced. Why then will you sin against innocent blood, to kill Dawood without a cause?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 19:6"}, "Saul listened to the voice of Jonathan: and Saul swore, \u201cAs the LORD lives, he shall not be put to death.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 19:7"}, "Jonathan called Dawood, and Jonathan showed him all those things. Then Jonathan brought Dawood to Saul, and he was in his\npresence, as before. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 19:8"}, "There was war again. Dawood went out, and fought with the Philistines, and killed them with a great slaughter; and they\nfled before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 19:9"}, "An evil spirit from the LORD was on Saul, as he sat in his house with his spear in his hand; and Dawood was playing with\nhis hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 19:10"}, "Saul sought to pin Dawood to the wall with the spear; but he slipped away out of Saul\u2019s presence, and he stuck the spear\ninto the wall. Dawood fled, and escaped that night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 19:11"}, "Saul sent messengers to Dawood\u2019s house, to watch him, and to kill him in the morning. Michal, Dawood\u2019s wife, told him,\nsaying, \u201cIf you don\u2019t save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be killed.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 19:12"}, "So Michal let Dawood down through the window. He went away, fled, and escaped.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 19:13"}, "Michal took the teraphim,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with inheritance\nrights to the household property."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and laid it in the bed, and put a pillow of goats\u2019 hair at its head, and covered it with\nclothes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 19:14"}, "When Saul sent messengers to take Dawood, she said, \u201cHe is sick.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 19:15"}, "Saul sent the messengers to see Dawood, saying, \u201cBring him up to me in the bed, that I may kill him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 19:16"}, "When the messengers came in, behold, the teraphim was in the bed, with the pillow of goats\u2019 hair at its head.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 19:17"}, "Saul said to Michal, \u201cWhy have you deceived me like this and let my enemy go, so that he has escaped?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Michal answered Saul, \u201cHe said to me, \u2018Let me go! Why should I kill you?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 19:18"}, "Now Dawood fled and escaped, and came to Samuel at Ramah, and told him all that Saul had done to him. He and Samuel went\nand lived in Naioth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 19:19"}, "Saul was told, saying, \u201cBehold, Dawood is at Naioth in Ramah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 19:20"}, "Saul sent messengers to seize Dawood: and when they saw the company of the prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing as\nhead over them, Allah\u2019s Spirit came on Saul\u2019s messengers, and they also prophesied.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 19:21"}, "When Saul was told, he sent other messengers, and they also prophesied. Saul sent messengers again the third time, and\nthey also prophesied. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 19:22"}, "Then he also went to Ramah, and came to the great well that is in Secu: and he asked, \u201cWhere are Samuel and Dawood?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["One said, \u201cBehold, they are at Naioth in Ramah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 19:23"}, "He went there to Naioth in Ramah. Then Allah\u2019s Spirit came on him also, and he went on, and prophesied, until he came to\nNaioth in Ramah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 19:24"}, "He also stripped off his clothes, and he also prophesied before Samuel, and lay down naked all that day and all that\nnight. Therefore they say, \u201cIs Saul also amongst the prophets?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 20:1"}, "Dawood fled from Naioth in Ramah, and came and said before Jonathan, \u201cWhat have I done? What is my iniquity? What is my\nsin before your father, that he seeks my life?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 20:2"}, "He said to him, \u201cFar from it; you will not die. Behold, my father does nothing either great or small, but that he\ndiscloses it to me. Why would my father hide this thing from me? It is not so.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 20:3"}, "Dawood swore moreover, and said, \u201cYour father knows well that I have found favour in your eyes; and he says, \u2018Don\u2019t let\nJonathan know this, lest he be grieved;\u2019 but truly as the LORD lives, and as your soul lives, there is but a step between me\nand death.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 20:4"}, "Then Jonathan said to Dawood, \u201cWhatever your soul desires, I will even do it for you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 20:5"}, "Dawood said to Jonathan, \u201cBehold, tomorrow is the new moon, and I should not fail to dine with the king; but let me go,\nthat I may hide myself in the field to the third day at evening.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 20:6"}, "If your father misses me at all, then say, \u2018Dawood earnestly asked leave of me that he might run to Bethlehem his city;\nfor it is the yearly sacrifice there for all the family.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 20:7"}, "If he says, \u2018It is well,\u2019 your servant shall have peace; but if he is angry, then know that evil is determined by him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 20:8"}, "Therefore deal kindly with your servant; for you have brought your servant into a covenant of the LORD with you; but if\nthere is iniquity in me, kill me yourself; for why should you bring me to your father?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 20:9"}, "Jonathan said, \u201cFar be it from you; for if I should at all know that evil were determined by my father to come on you,\nthen wouldn\u2019t I tell you that?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 20:10"}, "Then Dawood said to Jonathan, \u201cWho will tell me if your father answers you roughly?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 20:11"}, "Jonathan said to Dawood, \u201cCome! Let\u2019s go out into the field.\u201d They both went out into the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 20:12"}, "Jonathan said to Dawood, \u201cBy the LORD, Allah of Israel, when I have sounded my father about this time tomorrow, or the\nthird day, behold, if there is good towards Dawood, won\u2019t I then send to you, and disclose it to you?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 20:13"}, "The LORD do so to Jonathan, and more also, should it please my father to do you evil, if I don\u2019t disclose it to you, and\nsend you away, that you may go in peace. May the LORD be with you, as he has been with my father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 20:14"}, "You shall not only show me the loving kindness of the LORD while I still live, that I not die;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 20:15"}, "but you shall also not cut off your kindness from my house forever; no, not when the LORD has cut off every one of the\nenemies of Dawood from the surface of the earth.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 20:16"}, "So Jonathan made a covenant with Dawood\u2019s house, saying, \u201cThe LORD will require it at the hand of Dawood\u2019s enemies.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 20:17"}, "Jonathan caused Dawood to swear again, for the love that he had to him; for he loved him as he loved his own soul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 20:18"}, "Then Jonathan said to him, \u201cTomorrow is the new moon, and you will be missed, because your seat will be empty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 20:19"}, "When you have stayed three days, go down quickly, and come to the place where you hid yourself when this started, and\nremain by the stone Ezel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 20:20"}, "I will shoot three arrows on its side, as though I shot at a mark.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 20:21"}, "Behold, I will send the boy, saying, \u2018Go, find the arrows!\u2019 If I tell the boy, \u2018Behold, the arrows are on this side of\nyou. Take them;\u2019 then come; for there is peace to you and no danger, as the LORD lives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 20:22"}, "But if I say this to the boy, \u2018Behold, the arrows are beyond you;\u2019 then go your way; for the LORD has sent you away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 20:23"}, "Concerning the matter which you and I have spoken of, behold, the LORD is between you and me forever.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 20:24"}, "So Dawood hid himself in the field. When the new moon had come, the king sat himself down to eat food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 20:25"}, "The king sat on his seat, as at other times, even on the seat by the wall; and Jonathan stood up, and Abner sat by Saul\u2019s\nside, but Dawood\u2019s place was empty. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 20:26"}, "Nevertheless Saul didn\u2019t say anything that day, for he thought, \u201cSomething has happened to him. He is not clean. Surely\nhe is not clean.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 20:27"}, "On the next day after the new moon, the second day, Dawood\u2019s place was empty. Saul said to Jonathan his son, \u201cWhy doesn\u2019t\nthe son of Jesse come to eat, either yesterday, or today?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 20:28"}, "Jonathan answered Saul, \u201cDawood earnestly asked permission of me to go to Bethlehem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 20:29"}, "He said, \u2018Please let me go, for our family has a sacrifice in the city. My brother has commanded me to be there. Now, if\nI have found favour in your eyes, please let me go away and see my brothers.\u2019 Therefore he has not come to the king\u2019s table.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 20:30"}, "Then Saul\u2019s anger burnt against Jonathan, and he said to him, \u201cYou son of a perverse rebellious woman, don\u2019t I know that\nyou have chosen the son of Jesse to your own shame, and to the shame of your mother\u2019s nakedness?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 20:31"}, "For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, you will not be established, nor will your kingdom. Therefore now\nsend and bring him to me, for he shall surely die!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 20:32"}, "Jonathan answered Saul his father, and said to him, \u201cWhy should he be put to death? What has he done?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 20:33"}, "Saul cast his spear at him to strike him. By this Jonathan knew that his father was determined to put Dawood to death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 20:34"}, "So Jonathan arose from the table in fierce anger, and ate no food the second day of the month; for he was grieved for\nDawood, because his father had treated him shamefully. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 20:35"}, "In the morning, Jonathan went out into the field at the time appointed with Dawood, and a little boy with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1SA 20:36"}, "He said to his boy, \u201cRun, find now the arrows which I shoot.\u201d As the boy ran, he shot an arrow beyond him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1SA 20:37"}, "When the boy had come to the place of the arrow which Jonathan had shot, Jonathan cried after the boy, and said, \u201cIsn\u2019t\nthe arrow beyond you?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1SA 20:38"}, "Jonathan cried after the boy, \u201cGo fast! Hurry! Don\u2019t delay!\u201d Jonathan\u2019s boy gathered up the arrows, and came to his\nmaster. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1SA 20:39"}, "But the boy didn\u2019t know anything. Only Jonathan and Dawood knew the matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1SA 20:40"}, "Jonathan gave his weapons to his boy, and said to him, \u201cGo, carry them to the city.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1SA 20:41"}, "As soon as the boy was gone, Dawood arose out of the south, and fell on his face to the ground, and bowed himself three\ntimes. They kissed one another, and wept one with another, and Dawood wept the most.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1SA 20:42"}, "Jonathan said to Dawood, \u201cGo in peace, because we have both sworn in the LORD\u2019s name, saying, \u2018The LORD is between me and\nyou, and between my offspring and your offspring, forever.\u2019\u201d He arose and departed; and Jonathan went into the city.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 21:1"}, "Then Dawood came to Nob to Ahimelech the priest. Ahimelech came to meet Dawood trembling, and said to him, \u201cWhy are you\nalone, and no man with you?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 21:2"}, "Dawood said to Ahimelech the priest, \u201cThe king has commanded me to do something, and has said to me, \u2018Let no one know\nanything about the business about which I send you, and what I have commanded you. I have sent the young men to a certain\nplace.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 21:3"}, "Now therefore what is under your hand? Please give me five loaves of bread in my hand, or whatever is available.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 21:4"}, "The priest answered Dawood, and said, \u201cI have no common bread, but there is holy bread; if only the young men have kept\nthemselves from women.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 21:5"}, "Dawood answered the priest, and said to him, \u201cTruly, women have been kept from us as usual these three days. When I came\nout, the vessels of the young men were holy, though it was only a common journey. How much more then today shall their vessels\nbe holy?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 21:6"}, "So the priest gave him holy bread; for there was no bread there but the show bread that was taken from before the LORD, to\nput hot bread in the day when it was taken away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 21:7"}, "Now a certain man of the servants of Saul was there that day, detained before the LORD; and his name was Doeg the Edomite,\nthe best of the herdsmen who belonged to Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 21:8"}, "Dawood said to Ahimelech, \u201cIsn\u2019t there here under your hand spear or sword? For I have neither brought my sword nor my\nweapons with me, because the king\u2019s business required haste.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 21:9"}, "The priest said, \u201cBehold, the sword of Goliath the Philistine, whom you killed in the valley of Elah, is here wrapped in a\ncloth behind the ephod. If you would like to take that, take it; for there is no other except that here.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cThere is none like that. Give it to me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 21:10"}, "Dawood arose, and fled that day for fear of Saul, and went to Achish the king of Gath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 21:11"}, "The servants of Achish said to him, \u201cIsn\u2019t this Dawood the king of the land? Didn\u2019t they sing to one another about him in\ndances, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Saul has slain his thousands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Dawood his ten thousands?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 21:12"}, "Dawood laid up these words in his heart, and was very afraid of Achish the king of Gath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 21:13"}, "He changed his behaviour before them, and pretended to be insane in their hands, and scribbled on the doors of the gate,\nand let his spittle fall down on his beard. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 21:14"}, "Then Achish said to his servants, \u201cLook, you see the man is insane. Why then have you brought him to me?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 21:15"}, "Do I lack madmen, that you have brought this fellow to play the madman in my presence? Should this fellow come into my\nhouse?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 22:1"}, "Dawood therefore departed from there, and escaped to Adullam\u2019s cave. When his brothers and all his father\u2019s house heard\nit, they went down there to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 22:2"}, "Everyone who was in distress, everyone who was in debt, and everyone who was discontented, gathered themselves to him; and\nhe became captain over them. There were with him about four hundred men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 22:3"}, "Dawood went from there to Mizpeh of Moab, and he said to the king of Moab, \u201cPlease let my father and my mother come out\nwith you, until I know what Allah will do for me.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 22:4"}, "He brought them before the king of Moab; and they lived with him all the time that Dawood was in the stronghold.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 22:5"}, "The prophet Gad said to Dawood, \u201cDon\u2019t stay in the stronghold. Depart, and go into the land of Judah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Dawood departed, and came into the forest of Hereth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 22:6"}, "Saul heard that Dawood was discovered, with the men who were with him. Now Saul was sitting in Gibeah, under the tamarisk\ntree in Ramah, with his spear in his hand, and all his servants were standing around him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 22:7"}, "Saul said to his servants who stood around him, \u201cHear now, you Benjamites! Will the son of Jesse give everyone of you\nfields and vineyards? Will he make you all captains of thousands and captains of hundreds,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 22:8"}, "that all of you have conspired against me, and there is no one who discloses to me when my son makes a treaty with the son\nof Jesse, and there is none of you who is sorry for me, or discloses to me that my son has stirred up my servant against me, to\nlie in wait, as it is today?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 22:9"}, "Then Doeg the Edomite, who stood by the servants of Saul, answered and said, \u201cI saw the son of Jesse coming to Nob, to\nAhimelech the son of Ahitub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 22:10"}, "He enquired of the LORD for him, gave him food, and gave him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 22:11"}, "Then the king sent to call Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub, and all his father\u2019s house, the priests who were in\nNob; and they all came to the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 22:12"}, "Saul said, \u201cHear now, you son of Ahitub.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cHere I am, my lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 22:13"}, "Saul said to him, \u201cWhy have you conspired against me, you and the son of Jesse, in that you have given him bread, and a\nsword, and have enquired of Allah for him, that he should rise against me, to lie in wait, as it is today?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 22:14"}, "Then Ahimelech answered the king, and said, \u201cWho amongst all your servants is so faithful as Dawood, who is the king\u2019s\nson-in-law, captain of your body guard, and honoured in your house?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 22:15"}, "Have I today begun to enquire of Allah for him? Be it far from me! Don\u2019t let the king impute anything to his servant, nor\nto all the house of my father; for your servant knows nothing of all this, less or more.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 22:16"}, "The king said, \u201cYou shall surely die, Ahimelech, you, and all your father\u2019s house.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 22:17"}, "The king said to the guard who stood about him, \u201cTurn, and kill the priests of the LORD; because their hand also is with\nDawood, and because they knew that he fled, and didn\u2019t disclose it to me.\u201d But the servants of the king wouldn\u2019t put out their\nhand to fall on the priests of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 22:18"}, "The king said to Doeg, \u201cTurn and attack the priests!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Doeg the Edomite turned, and he attacked the priests, and he killed on that day eighty-five people who wore a linen ephod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 22:19"}, "He struck Nob, the city of the priests, with the edge of the sword, both men and women, children and nursing babies, and\ncattle and donkeys and sheep, with the edge of the sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 22:20"}, "One of the sons of Ahimelech, the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar, escaped, and fled after Dawood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 22:21"}, "Abiathar told Dawood that Saul had slain the LORD\u2019s priests.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 22:22"}, "Dawood said to Abiathar, \u201cI knew on that day, when Doeg the Edomite was there, that he would surely tell Saul. I am\nresponsible for the death of all the persons of your father\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 22:23"}, "Stay with me. Don\u2019t be afraid, for he who seeks my life seeks your life. For you will be safe with me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 23:1"}, "Dawood was told, \u201cBehold, the Philistines are fighting against Keilah, and are robbing the threshing floors.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 23:2"}, "Therefore Dawood enquired of the LORD, saying, \u201cShall I go and strike these Philistines?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said to Dawood, \u201cGo strike the Philistines, and save Keilah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 23:3"}, "Dawood\u2019s men said to him, \u201cBehold, we are afraid here in Judah. How much more then if we go to Keilah against the armies\nof the Philistines?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 23:4"}, "Then Dawood enquired of the LORD yet again. The LORD answered him, and said, \u201cArise, go down to Keilah; for I will deliver\nthe Philistines into your hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 23:5"}, "Dawood and his men went to Keilah, and fought with the Philistines, and brought away their livestock, and killed them with\na great slaughter. So Dawood saved the inhabitants of Keilah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 23:6"}, "When Abiathar the son of Ahimelech fled to Dawood to Keilah, he came down with an ephod in his hand.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 23:7"}, "Saul was told that Dawood had come to Keilah. Saul said, \u201cAllah has delivered him into my hand; for he is shut in by\nentering into a town that has gates and bars.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 23:8"}, "Saul summoned all the people to war, to go down to Keilah, to besiege Dawood and his men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 23:9"}, "Dawood knew that Saul was devising mischief against him; and he said to Abiathar the priest, \u201cBring the ephod here.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 23:10"}, "Then Dawood said, \u201cO LORD, Allah of Israel, your servant has surely heard that Saul seeks to come to Keilah, to destroy\nthe city for my sake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 23:11"}, "Will the men of Keilah deliver me up into his hand? Will Saul come down, as your servant has heard? LORD, Allah of\nIsrael, I beg you, tell your servant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cHe will come down.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 23:12"}, "Then Dawood said, \u201cWill the men of Keilah deliver me and my men into the hand of Saul?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cThey will deliver you up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 23:13"}, "Then Dawood and his men, who were about six hundred, arose and departed out of Keilah, and went wherever they could go.\nSaul was told that Dawood was escaped from Keilah; and he gave up going there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 23:14"}, "Dawood stayed in the wilderness in the strongholds, and remained in the hill country in the wilderness of Ziph. Saul\nsought him every day, but Allah didn\u2019t deliver him into his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 23:15"}, "Dawood saw that Saul had come out to seek his life. Dawood was in the wilderness of Ziph in the wood.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 23:16"}, "Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, arose, and went to Dawood into the woods, and strengthened his hand in Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 23:17"}, "He said to him, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid; for the hand of Saul my father won\u2019t find you; and you will be king over Israel, and I\nwill be next to you; and Saul my father knows that also.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 23:18"}, "They both made a covenant before the LORD. Then Dawood stayed in the woods, and Jonathan went to his house.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 23:19"}, "Then the Ziphites came up to Saul to Gibeah, saying, \u201cDoesn\u2019t Dawood hide himself with us in the strongholds in the\nwoods, in the hill of Hachilah, which is on the south of the desert?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 23:20"}, "Now therefore, O king, come down. According to all the desire of your soul to come down; and our part will be to deliver\nhim up into the king\u2019s hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 23:21"}, "Saul said, \u201cYou are blessed by the LORD; for you have had compassion on me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 23:22"}, "Please go make yet more sure, and know and see his place where his haunt is, and who has seen him there; for I have been\ntold that he is very cunning. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 23:23"}, "See therefore, and take knowledge of all the lurking places where he hides himself, and come again to me with certainty,\nand I will go with you. It shall happen, if he is in the land, that I will search him out amongst all the thousands of Judah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 23:24"}, "They arose, and went to Ziph before Saul: but Dawood and his men were in the wilderness of Maon, in the Arabah on the\nsouth of the desert. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 23:25"}, "Saul and his men went to seek him. When Dawood was told, he went down to the rock, and stayed in the wilderness of Maon.\nWhen Saul heard that, he pursued Dawood in the wilderness of Maon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 23:26"}, "Saul went on this side of the mountain, and Dawood and his men on that side of the mountain; and Dawood hurried to get\naway for fear of Saul; for Saul and his men surrounded Dawood and his men to take them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 23:27"}, "But a messenger came to Saul, saying, \u201cHurry and come; for the Philistines have made a raid on the land!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 23:28"}, "So Saul returned from pursuing Dawood, and went against the Philistines. Therefore they called that place Sela\nHammahlekoth.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cSela Hammahlekoth\u201d means \u201crock of\nparting\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 23:29"}, "Dawood went up from there, and lived in the strongholds of En Gedi.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 24:1"}, "When Saul had returned from following the Philistines, he was told, \u201cBehold, Dawood is in the wilderness of En Gedi.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 24:2"}, "Then Saul took three thousand chosen men out of all Israel, and went to seek Dawood and his men on the rocks of the wild\ngoats. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 24:3"}, "He came to the sheep pens by the way, where there was a cave; and Saul went in to relieve himself. Now Dawood and his men\nwere staying in the innermost parts of the cave. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 24:4"}, "Dawood\u2019s men said to him, \u201cBehold, the day of which the LORD said to you, \u2018Behold, I will deliver your enemy into your\nhand, and you shall do to him as it shall seem good to you.\u2019\u201d Then Dawood arose, and cut off the skirt of Saul\u2019s robe secretly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 24:5"}, "Afterward, Dawood\u2019s heart struck him, because he had cut off Saul\u2019s skirt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 24:6"}, "He said to his men, \u201cThe LORD forbid that I should do this thing to my lord, the LORD\u2019s anointed, to stretch out my hand\nagainst him, since he is the LORD\u2019s anointed.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 24:7"}, "So Dawood checked his men with these words, and didn\u2019t allow them to rise against Saul. Saul rose up out of the cave, and\nwent on his way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 24:8"}, "Dawood also arose afterward, and went out of the cave, and cried after Saul, saying, \u201cMy lord the king!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When Saul looked behind him, Dawood bowed with his face to the earth, and showed respect.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 24:9"}, "Dawood said to Saul, \u201cWhy do you listen to men\u2019s words, saying, \u2018Behold, Dawood seeks to harm you?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 24:10"}, "Behold, today your eyes have seen how the LORD had delivered you today into my hand in the cave. Some urged me to kill\nyou; but I spared you; and I said, I will not stretch out my hand against my lord; for he is the LORD\u2019s anointed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 24:11"}, "Moreover, my father, behold, yes, see the skirt of your robe in my hand; for in that I cut off the skirt of your robe,\nand didn\u2019t kill you, know and see that there is neither evil nor disobedience in my hand, and I have not sinned against you,\nthough you hunt for my life to take it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 24:12"}, "May the LORD judge between me and you, and may the LORD avenge me of you; but my hand will not be on you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 24:13"}, "As the proverb of the ancients says, \u2018Out of the wicked comes wickedness;\u2019 but my hand will not be on you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 24:14"}, "Against whom has the king of Israel come out? Whom do you pursue? A dead dog? A flea?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 24:15"}, "May the LORD therefore be judge, and give sentence between me and you, and see, and plead my cause, and deliver me out of\nyour hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 24:16"}, "It came to pass, when Dawood had finished speaking these words to Saul, that Saul said, \u201cIs that your voice, my son\nDawood?\u201d Saul lifted up his voice, and wept. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 24:17"}, "He said to Dawood, \u201cYou are more righteous than I; for you have done good to me, whereas I have done evil to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 24:18"}, "You have declared today how you have dealt well with me, because when the LORD had delivered me up into your hand, you\ndidn\u2019t kill me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 24:19"}, "For if a man finds his enemy, will he let him go away unharmed? Therefore may the LORD reward you good for that which you\nhave done to me today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 24:20"}, "Now, behold, I know that you will surely be king, and that the kingdom of Israel will be established in your hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 24:21"}, "Swear now therefore to me by the LORD, that you will not cut off my offspring after me, and that you will not destroy my\nname out of my father\u2019s house.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 24:22"}, "Dawood swore to Saul. Saul went home, but Dawood and his men went up to the stronghold.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 25:1"}, "Samuel died; and all Israel gathered themselves together, and mourned for him, and buried him at his house at Ramah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Dawood arose, and went down to the wilderness of Paran. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 25:2"}, "There was a man in Maon, whose possessions were in Carmel; and the man was very great. He had three thousand sheep and a\nthousand goats; and he was shearing his sheep in Carmel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 25:3"}, "Now the name of the man was Nabal; and the name of his wife Abigail. This woman was intelligent and had a beautiful face;\nbut the man was surly and evil in his doings. He was of the house of Caleb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 25:4"}, "Dawood heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 25:5"}, "Dawood sent ten young men, and Dawood said to the young men, \u201cGo up to Carmel, and go to Nabal, and greet him in my name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 25:6"}, "Tell him, \u2018Long life to you! Peace be to you! Peace be to your house! Peace be to all that you have!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 25:7"}, "Now I have heard that you have shearers. Your shepherds have now been with us, and we didn\u2019t harm them. Nothing was\nmissing from them all the time they were in Carmel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 25:8"}, "Ask your young men, and they will tell you. Therefore let the young men find favour in your eyes; for we come on a good\nday. Please give whatever comes to your hand, to your servants, and to your son Dawood.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 25:9"}, "When Dawood\u2019s young men came, they spoke to Nabal all those words in the name of Dawood, and waited.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 25:10"}, "Nabal answered Dawood\u2019s servants, and said, \u201cWho is Dawood? Who is the son of Jesse? There are many servants who break\naway from their masters these days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 25:11"}, "Shall I then take my bread, my water, and my meat that I have killed for my shearers, and give it to men who I don\u2019t know\nwhere they come from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 25:12"}, "So Dawood\u2019s young men turned on their way, and went back, and came and told him all these words.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 25:13"}, "Dawood said to his men, \u201cEvery man put on his sword!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Every man put on his sword. Dawood also put on his sword. About four hundred men followed Dawood, and two hundred stayed by\nthe baggage. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 25:14"}, "But one of the young men told Abigail, Nabal\u2019s wife, saying, \u201cBehold, Dawood sent messengers out of the wilderness to\nGreet our master; and he insulted them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 25:15"}, "But the men were very good to us, and we were not harmed, and we didn\u2019t miss anything, as long as we went with them, when\nwe were in the fields. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 25:16"}, "They were a wall to us both by night and by day, all the while we were with them keeping the sheep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 25:17"}, "Now therefore know and consider what you will do; for evil is determined against our master, and against all his house;\nfor he is such a worthless fellow that one can\u2019t speak to him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 25:18"}, "Then Abigail hurried and took two hundred loaves of bread, two containers of wine, five sheep ready dressed, five\nseahs", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 seah is about 7 litres or 1.9 gallons or 0.8\npecks"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of parched grain, one hundred clusters of raisins, and two hundred cakes of figs, and laid them on donkeys.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 25:19"}, "She said to her young men, \u201cGo on before me. Behold, I am coming after you.\u201d But she didn\u2019t tell her husband, Nabal.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 25:20"}, "As she rode on her donkey, and came down by the covert of the mountain, that behold, Dawood and his men came down towards\nher, and she met them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 25:21"}, "Now Dawood had said, \u201cSurely in vain I have kept all that this fellow has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missed\nof all that pertained to him. He has returned me evil for good. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 25:22"}, "Allah do so to the enemies of Dawood, and more also, if I leave of all that belongs to him by the morning light so much\nas one who urinates on a wall.\u201d ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, male."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 25:23"}, "When Abigail saw Dawood, she hurried and got off her donkey, and fell before Dawood on her face, and bowed herself to the\nground. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 25:24"}, "She fell at his feet, and said, \u201cOn me, my lord, on me be the blame! Please let your servant speak in your ears. Hear the\nwords of your servant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 25:25"}, "Please don\u2019t let my lord pay attention to this worthless fellow, Nabal; for as his name is, so is he.\nNabal", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cNabal\u201d means \u201cfoolish\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " is his name, and folly is with him; but I, your servant, didn\u2019t see my\nlord\u2019s young men, whom you sent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 25:26"}, "Now therefore, my lord, as the LORD lives, and as your soul lives, since the LORD has withheld you from blood guiltiness,\nand from avenging yourself with your own hand, now therefore let your enemies, and those who seek evil to my lord, be as Nabal.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 25:27"}, "Now this present which your servant has brought to my lord, let it be given to the young men who follow my lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 25:28"}, "Please forgive the trespass of your servant. For the LORD will certainly make my lord a sure house, because my lord\nfights the LORD\u2019s battles. Evil will not be found in you all your days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 25:29"}, "Though men may rise up to pursue you, and to seek your soul, yet the soul of my lord will be bound in the bundle of life\nwith Allah your LORD. He will sling out the souls of your enemies, as from the hollow of a sling.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 25:30"}, "It will come to pass, when the LORD has done to my lord according to all the good that he has spoken concerning you, and\nhas appointed you prince over Israel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 25:31"}, "that this shall be no grief to you, nor offence of heart to my lord, either that you have shed blood without cause, or\nthat my lord has avenged himself. When the LORD has dealt well with my lord, then remember your servant.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1SA 25:32"}, "Dawood said to Abigail, \u201cBlessed is the LORD, Allah of Israel, who sent you today to meet me!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1SA 25:33"}, "Blessed is your discretion, and blessed are you, who have kept me today from blood guiltiness, and from avenging myself\nwith my own hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1SA 25:34"}, "For indeed, as the LORD, Allah of Israel, lives, who has withheld me from harming you, unless you had hurried and come to\nmeet me, surely there wouldn\u2019t have been left to Nabal by the morning light so much as one who urinates on a\nwall.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, one male."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1SA 25:35"}, "So Dawood received from her hand that which she had brought him. Then he said to her, \u201cGo up in peace to your house.\nBehold, I have listened to your voice, and have granted your request.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1SA 25:36"}, "Abigail came to Nabal; and behold, he held a feast in his house, like the feast of a king. Nabal\u2019s heart was merry within\nhim, for he was very drunk. Therefore she told him nothing until the morning light.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1SA 25:37"}, "In the morning, when the wine had gone out of Nabal, his wife told him these things, and his heart died within him, and\nhe became as a stone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1SA 25:38"}, "About ten days later, the LORD struck Nabal, so that he died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1SA 25:39"}, "When Dawood heard that Nabal was dead, he said, \u201cBlessed is the LORD, who has pleaded the cause of my reproach from the\nhand of Nabal, and has kept back his servant from evil. The LORD has returned the evildoing of Nabal on his own head.\u201d Dawood\nsent and spoke concerning Abigail, to take her to himself as wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1SA 25:40"}, "When Dawood\u2019s servants had come to Abigail to Carmel, they spoke to her, saying, \u201cDawood has sent us to you, to take you\nto him as wife.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1SA 25:41"}, "She arose, and bowed herself with her face to the earth, and said, \u201cBehold, your servant is a servant to wash the feet of\nthe servants of my lord.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1SA 25:42"}, "Abigail hurried, and arose, and rode on a donkey, with five ladies of hers who followed her; and she went after the\nmessengers of Dawood, and became his wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1SA 25:43"}, "Dawood also took Ahinoam of Jezreel; and they both became his wives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1SA 25:44"}, "Now Saul had given Michal his daughter, Dawood\u2019s wife, to Palti the son of Laish, who was of Gallim.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 26:1"}, "The Ziphites came to Saul to Gibeah, saying, \u201cDoesn\u2019t Dawood hide himself in the hill of Hachilah, which is before the\ndesert?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 26:2"}, "Then Saul arose, and went down to the wilderness of Ziph, having three thousand chosen men of Israel with him, to seek\nDawood in the wilderness of Ziph. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 26:3"}, "Saul encamped in the hill of Hachilah, which is before the desert, by the way. But Dawood stayed in the wilderness, and he\nsaw that Saul came after him into the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 26:4"}, "Dawood therefore sent out spies, and understood that Saul had certainly come.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 26:5"}, "Then Dawood arose, and came to the place where Saul had encamped; and Dawood saw the place where Saul lay, with Abner the\nson of Ner, the captain of his army. Saul lay within the place of the wagons, and the people were encamped around him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 26:6"}, "Then Dawood answered and said to Ahimelech the Hittite, and to Abishai the son of Zeruiah, brother of Joab, saying, \u201cWho\nwill go down with me to Saul to the camp?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Abishai said, \u201cI will go down with you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 26:7"}, "So Dawood and Abishai came to the people by night: and, behold, Saul lay sleeping within the place of the wagons, with his\nspear stuck in the ground at his head; and Abner and the people lay around him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 26:8"}, "Then Abishai said to Dawood, \u201cAllah has delivered up your enemy into your hand today. Now therefore please let me strike\nhim with the spear to the earth at one stroke, and I will not strike him the second time.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 26:9"}, "Dawood said to Abishai, \u201cDon\u2019t destroy him; for who can stretch out his hand against the LORD\u2019s anointed, and be\nguiltless?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 26:10"}, "Dawood said, \u201cAs the LORD lives, the LORD will strike him; or his day shall come to die; or he shall go down into battle\nand perish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 26:11"}, "The LORD forbid that I should stretch out my hand against the LORD\u2019s anointed; but now please take the spear that is at\nhis head, and the jar of water, and let\u2019s go.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 26:12"}, "So Dawood took the spear and the jar of water from Saul\u2019s head; and they went away: and no man saw it, or knew it, nor\ndid any awake; for they were all asleep, because a deep sleep from the LORD had fallen on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 26:13"}, "Then Dawood went over to the other side, and stood on the top of the mountain afar off; a great space being between them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 26:14"}, "and Dawood cried to the people, and to Abner the son of Ner, saying, \u201cDon\u2019t you answer, Abner?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Abner answered, \u201cWho are you who cries to the king?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 26:15"}, "Dawood said to Abner, \u201cAren\u2019t you a man? Who is like you in Israel? Why then have you not kept watch over your lord, the\nking? For one of the people came in to destroy the king your lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 26:16"}, "This thing isn\u2019t good that you have done. As the LORD lives, you are worthy to die, because you have not kept watch over\nyour lord, the LORD\u2019s anointed. Now see where the king\u2019s spear is, and the jar of water that was at his head.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 26:17"}, "Saul knew Dawood\u2019s voice, and said, \u201cIs this your voice, my son Dawood?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cIt is my voice, my lord, O king.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 26:18"}, "He said, \u201cWhy does my lord pursue his servant? For what have I done? What evil is in my hand?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 26:19"}, "Now therefore, please let my lord the king hear the words of his servant. If it is so that the LORD has stirred you up\nagainst me, let him accept an offering. But if it is the children of men, they are cursed before the LORD; for they have driven\nme out today that I shouldn\u2019t cling to the LORD\u2019s inheritance, saying, \u2018Go, serve other gods!\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 26:20"}, "Now therefore, don\u2019t let my blood fall to the earth away from the presence of the LORD; for the king of Israel has come\nout to seek a flea, as when one hunts a partridge in the mountains.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 26:21"}, "Then Saul said, \u201cI have sinned. Return, my son Dawood; for I will no more do you harm, because my life was precious in\nyour eyes today. Behold, I have played the fool, and have erred exceedingly.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 26:22"}, "Dawood answered, \u201cBehold the spear, O king! Then let one of the young men come over and get it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 26:23"}, "The LORD will render to every man his righteousness and his faithfulness; because the LORD delivered you into my hand\ntoday, and I wouldn\u2019t stretch out my hand against the LORD\u2019s anointed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 26:24"}, "Behold, as your life was respected today in my eyes, so let my life be respected in the LORD\u2019s eyes, and let him deliver\nme out of all oppression.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 26:25"}, "Then Saul said to Dawood, \u201cYou are blessed, my son Dawood. You will both do mightily, and will surely prevail.\u201d So Dawood\nwent his way, and Saul returned to his place. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 27:1"}, "Dawood said in his heart, \u201cI will now perish one day by the hand of Saul. There is nothing better for me than that I\nshould escape into the land of the Philistines; and Saul will despair of me, to seek me any more in all the borders of Israel.\nSo shall I escape out of his hand.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 27:2"}, "Dawood arose, and passed over, he and the six hundred men who were with him, to Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 27:3"}, "Dawood lived with Achish at Gath, he and his men, every man with his household, even Dawood with his two wives, Ahinoam\nthe Jezreelitess, and Abigail the Carmelitess, Nabal\u2019s wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 27:4"}, "Saul was told that Dawood had fled to Gath: and he sought no more again for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 27:5"}, "Dawood said to Achish, \u201cIf now I have found favour in your eyes, let them give me a place in one of the cities in the\ncountry, that I may dwell there. For why should your servant dwell in the royal city with you?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 27:6"}, "Then Achish gave him Ziklag that day: therefore Ziklag belongs to the kings of Judah to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 27:7"}, "The number of the days that Dawood lived in the country of the Philistines was a full year and four months.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 27:8"}, "Dawood and his men went up and raided the Geshurites, the Girzites, and the Amalekites; for those were the inhabitants of\nthe land, who were of old, on the way to Shur, even to the land of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 27:9"}, "Dawood struck the land, and saved no man or woman alive, and took away the sheep, the cattle, the donkeys, the camels, and\nthe clothing. Then he returned, and came to Achish. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 27:10"}, "Achish said, \u201cAgainst whom have you made a raid today?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cAgainst the South of Judah, against the South of the Jerahmeelites, and against the South of the Kenites.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 27:11"}, "Dawood saved neither man nor woman alive, to bring them to Gath, saying, \u201cLest they should tell about us, saying, \u2018Dawood\ndid this, and this has been his way all the time he has lived in the country of the Philistines.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 27:12"}, "Achish believed Dawood, saying, \u201cHe has made his people Israel utterly to abhor him. Therefore he will be my servant\nforever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 28:1"}, "In those days, the Philistines gathered their armies together for warfare, to fight with Israel. Achish said to Dawood,\n\u201cKnow assuredly that you will go out with me in the army, you and your men.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 28:2"}, "Dawood said to Achish, \u201cTherefore you will know what your servant can do.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Achish said to Dawood, \u201cTherefore I will make you my bodyguard forever.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 28:3"}, "Now Samuel was dead, and all Israel had mourned for him, and buried him in Ramah, even in his own city. Saul had sent away\nthose who had familiar spirits and the wizards out of the land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 28:4"}, "The Philistines gathered themselves together, and came and encamped in Shunem; and Saul gathered all Israel together, and\nthey encamped in Gilboa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 28:5"}, "When Saul saw the army of the Philistines, he was afraid, and his heart trembled greatly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 28:6"}, "When Saul enquired of the LORD, the LORD didn\u2019t answer him by dreams, by Urim, or by prophets.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 28:7"}, "Then Saul said to his servants, \u201cSeek for me a woman who has a familiar spirit, that I may go to her, and enquire of her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["His servants said to him, \u201cBehold, there is a woman who has a familiar spirit at Endor.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 28:8"}, "Saul disguised himself and put on other clothing, and went, he and two men with him, and they came to the woman by night.\nThen he said, \u201cPlease consult for me by the familiar spirit, and bring me up whomever I shall name to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 28:9"}, "The woman said to him, \u201cBehold, you know what Saul has done, how he has cut off those who have familiar spirits, and the\nwizards, out of the land. Why then do you lay a snare for my life, to cause me to die?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 28:10"}, "Saul swore to her by the LORD, saying, \u201cAs the LORD lives, no punishment will happen to you for this thing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 28:11"}, "Then the woman said, \u201cWhom shall I bring up to you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cBring Samuel up for me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 28:12"}, "When the woman saw Samuel, she cried with a loud voice; and the woman spoke to Saul, saying, \u201cWhy have you deceived me?\nFor you are Saul!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 28:13"}, "The king said to her, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid! What do you see?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman said to Saul, \u201cI see a god coming up out of the earth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 28:14"}, "He said to her, \u201cWhat does he look like?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cAn old man comes up. He is covered with a robe.\u201d Saul perceived that it was Samuel, and he bowed with his face to\nthe ground, and showed respect. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 28:15"}, "Samuel said to Saul, \u201cWhy have you disturbed me, to bring me up?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Saul answered, \u201cI am very distressed; for the Philistines make war against me, and Allah has departed from me, and answers\nme no more, by prophets, or by dreams. Therefore I have called you, that you may make known to me what I shall do.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 28:16"}, "Samuel said, \u201cWhy then do you ask me, since the LORD has departed from you and has become your adversary?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 28:17"}, "The LORD has done to you as he spoke by me. The LORD has torn the kingdom out of your hand, and given it to your\nneighbour, even to Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 28:18"}, "Because you didn\u2019t obey the LORD\u2019s voice, and didn\u2019t execute his fierce wrath on Amalek, therefore the LORD has done this\nthing to you today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 28:19"}, "Moreover the LORD will deliver Israel also with you into the hand of the Philistines; and tomorrow you and your sons will\nbe with me. The LORD will deliver the army of Israel also into the hand of the Philistines.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 28:20"}, "Then Saul fell immediately his full length on the earth, and was terrified, because of Samuel\u2019s words. There was no\nstrength in him; for he had eaten no bread all day long or all night long.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 28:21"}, "The woman came to Saul, and saw that he was very troubled, and said to him, \u201cBehold, your servant has listened to your\nvoice, and I have put my life in my hand, and have listened to your words which you spoke to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 28:22"}, "Now therefore, please listen also to the voice of your servant, and let me set a morsel of bread before you. Eat, that\nyou may have strength, when you go on your way.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 28:23"}, "But he refused, and said, \u201cI will not eat.\u201d But his servants, together with the woman, constrained him; and he listened\nto their voice. So he arose from the earth and sat on the bed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 28:24"}, "The woman had a fattened calf in the house. She hurried and killed it; and she took flour, and kneaded it, and baked\nunleavened bread of it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 28:25"}, "She brought it before Saul, and before his servants; and they ate. Then they rose up, and went away that night.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 29:1"}, "Now the Philistines gathered together all their armies to Aphek; and the Israelites encamped by the spring which is in\nJezreel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 29:2"}, "The lords of the Philistines passed on by hundreds and by thousands; and Dawood and his men passed on in the rear with\nAchish. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 29:3"}, "Then the princes of the Philistines said, \u201cWhat about these Hebrews?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Achish said to the princes of the Philistines, \u201cIsn\u2019t this Dawood, the servant of Saul the king of Israel, who has been with\nme these days, or rather these years? I have found no fault in him since he fell away until today.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 29:4"}, "But the princes of the Philistines were angry with him; and the princes of the Philistines said to him, \u201cMake the man\nreturn, that he may go back to his place where you have appointed him, and let him not go down with us to battle, lest in the\nbattle he become an adversary to us. For with what should this fellow reconcile himself to his lord? Should it not be with the\nheads of these men? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 29:5"}, "Isn\u2019t this Dawood, of whom people sang to one another in dances, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Saul has slain his thousands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Dawood his ten thousands?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 29:6"}, "Then Achish called Dawood, and said to him, \u201cAs the LORD lives, you have been upright, and your going out and your coming\nin with me in the army is good in my sight; for I have not found evil in you since the day of your coming to me to this day.\nNevertheless, the lords don\u2019t favour you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 29:7"}, "Therefore now return, and go in peace, that you not displease the lords of the Philistines.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 29:8"}, "Dawood said to Achish, \u201cBut what have I done? What have you found in your servant so long as I have been before you to\nthis day, that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 29:9"}, "Achish answered Dawood, \u201cI know that you are good in my sight, as an angel of Allah. Notwithstanding the princes of the\nPhilistines have said, \u2018He shall not go up with us to the battle.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 29:10"}, "Therefore now rise up early in the morning with the servants of your lord who have come with you; and as soon as you are\nup early in the morning, and have light, depart.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 29:11"}, "So Dawood rose up early, he and his men, to depart in the morning, to return into the land of the Philistines, and the\nPhilistines went up to Jezreel. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 30"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 30:1"}, "When Dawood and his men had come to Ziklag on the third day, the Amalekites had made a raid on the South, and on Ziklag,\nand had struck Ziklag, and burnt it with fire, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 30:2"}, "and had taken captive the women and all who were in it, both small and great. They didn\u2019t kill any, but carried them off,\nand went their way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 30:3"}, "When Dawood and his men came to the city, behold, it was burnt with fire; and their wives, their sons, and their daughters\nwere taken captive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 30:4"}, "Then Dawood and the people who were with him lifted up their voice and wept until they had no more power to weep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 30:5"}, "Dawood\u2019s two wives were taken captive, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 30:6"}, "Dawood was greatly distressed; for the people spoke of stoning him, because the souls of all the people were grieved,\nevery man for his sons and for his daughters; but Dawood strengthened himself in the LORD his Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 30:7"}, "Dawood said to Abiathar the priest, the son of Ahimelech, \u201cPlease bring the ephod here to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Abiathar brought the ephod to Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 30:8"}, "Dawood enquired of the LORD, saying, \u201cIf I pursue after this troop, will I overtake them?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered him, \u201cPursue; for you will surely overtake them, and will without fail recover all.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 30:9"}, "So Dawood went, he and the six hundred men who were with him, and came to the brook Besor, where those who were left\nbehind stayed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 30:10"}, "But Dawood pursued, he and four hundred men; for two hundred stayed behind, who were so faint that they couldn\u2019t go over\nthe brook Besor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 30:11"}, "They found an Egyptian in the field, and brought him to Dawood, and gave him bread, and he ate; and they gave him water\nto drink. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 30:12"}, "They gave him a piece of a cake of figs, and two clusters of raisins. When he had eaten, his spirit came again to him;\nfor he had eaten no bread, and drank no water for three days and three nights.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 30:13"}, "Dawood asked him, \u201cTo whom do you belong? Where are you from?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am a young man of Egypt, servant to an Amalekite; and my master left me, because three days ago I got sick.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1SA 30:14"}, "We made a raid on the South of the Cherethites, and on that which belongs to Judah, and on the South of Caleb; and we\nburnt Ziklag with fire.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1SA 30:15"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cWill you bring me down to this troop?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cSwear to me by Allah that you will not kill me and not deliver me up into the hands of my master, and I will bring\nyou down to this troop.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1SA 30:16"}, "When he had brought him down, behold, they were spread around over all the ground, eating, drinking, and dancing, because\nof all the great plunder that they had taken out of the land of the Philistines, and out of the land of Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1SA 30:17"}, "Dawood struck them from the twilight even to the evening of the next day. Not a man of them escaped from there, except\nfour hundred young men, who rode on camels and fled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1SA 30:18"}, "Dawood recovered all that the Amalekites had taken, and Dawood rescued his two wives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1SA 30:19"}, "There was nothing lacking to them, neither small nor great, neither sons nor daughters, neither plunder, nor anything\nthat they had taken to them. Dawood brought back all. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1SA 30:20"}, "Dawood took all the flocks and the herds, which they drove before those other livestock, and said, \u201cThis is Dawood\u2019s\nplunder.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1SA 30:21"}, "Dawood came to the two hundred men, who were so faint that they could not follow Dawood, whom also they had made to stay\nat the brook Besor; and they went out to meet Dawood, and to meet the people who were with him. When Dawood came near to the\npeople, he greeted them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1SA 30:22"}, "Then all the wicked men and worthless fellows, of those who went with Dawood, answered and said, \u201cBecause they didn\u2019t go\nwith us, we will not give them anything of the plunder that we have recovered, except to every man his wife and his children,\nthat he may lead them away, and depart.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1SA 30:23"}, "Then Dawood said, \u201cDo not do so, my brothers, with that which the LORD has given to us, who has preserved us, and\ndelivered the troop that came against us into our hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1SA 30:24"}, "Who will listen to you in this matter? For as his share is who goes down to the battle, so shall his share be who stays\nwith the baggage. They shall share alike.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1SA 30:25"}, "It was so from that day forward, that he made it a statute and an ordinance for Israel to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1SA 30:26"}, "When Dawood came to Ziklag, he sent some of the plunder to the elders of Judah, even to his friends, saying, \u201cBehold, a\npresent for you from the plunder of the LORD\u2019s enemies.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1SA 30:27"}, "He sent it to those who were in Bethel, to those who were in Ramoth of the South, to those who were in Jattir,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1SA 30:28"}, "to those who were in Aroer, to those who were in Siphmoth, to those who were in Eshtemoa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1SA 30:29"}, "to those who were in Racal, to those who were in the cities of the Jerahmeelites, to those who were in the cities of the\nKenites, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1SA 30:30"}, "to those who were in Hormah, to those who were in Borashan, to those who were in Athach,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 30:31"}, "to those who were in Hebron, and to all the places where Dawood himself and his men used to stay.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "31", "sid": "1SA 31"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1SA 31:1"}, "Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel fled from before the Philistines, and fell down slain on\nMount Gilboa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1SA 31:2"}, "The Philistines overtook Saul and on his sons; and the Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malchishua, the sons of\nSaul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1SA 31:3"}, "The battle went hard against Saul, and the archers overtook him; and he was greatly distressed by reason of the archers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1SA 31:4"}, "Then Saul said to his armour bearer, \u201cDraw your sword, and thrust me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and\nthrust me through, and abuse me!\u201d But his armour bearer would not; for he was terrified. Therefore Saul took his sword, and\nfell on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1SA 31:5"}, "When his armour bearer saw that Saul was dead, he likewise fell on his sword, and died with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1SA 31:6"}, "So Saul died, and his three sons, and his armour bearer, and all his men, that same day together.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1SA 31:7"}, "When the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley, and those who were beyond the Jordan, saw that the men of\nIsrael fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned the cities and fled; and the Philistines came and lived in\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1SA 31:8"}, "On the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1SA 31:9"}, "They cut off his head, stripped off his armour, and sent into the land of the Philistines all around, to carry the news to\nthe house of their idols, and to the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1SA 31:10"}, "They put his armour in the house of the Ashtaroth, and they fastened his body to the wall of Beth Shan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1SA 31:11"}, "When the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead heard what the Philistines had done to Saul,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1SA 31:12"}, "all the valiant men arose, went all night, and took the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth\nShan; and they came to Jabesh, and burnt them there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1SA 31:13"}, "They took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["31:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, salt cedar"]}], "caller": "+"}, " tree in Jabesh, and fasted seven days.\n"]}]}